WEBVTT

00:14.416 --> 00:17.000
[man over radio]
We have a place, a compound.

00:17.833 --> 00:19.000
We have a community.

00:19.083 --> 00:20.416
[static]

00:20.500 --> 00:21.916
It's safe here.

00:23.833 --> 00:25.208
How many of you are there?

00:26.708 --> 00:28.625
Are any of them children?

00:30.208 --> 00:32.791
Because the fastest way
to get here is by the river,

00:32.875 --> 00:35.625
and I don't think
you could make it with kids.

00:46.500 --> 00:48.708
[woman] Listen to me.
I'm only gonna say this once.

00:49.500 --> 00:52.375
We are going on the trip now.
It's going to be rough.

00:52.458 --> 00:55.083
It's gonna feel like
it's going on for a long time,

00:55.166 --> 00:57.041
so it's gonna be hard to stay alert.

00:57.125 --> 01:01.083
It's gonna be even harder to be quiet,
but you have to do both.

01:01.166 --> 01:05.958
You have to do every single thing I say
or we will not make it.

01:06.041 --> 01:07.166
Understand?

01:09.041 --> 01:13.625
Under no circumstance are you allowed
to take off your blindfold.

01:13.708 --> 01:16.333
If I find that you have, I will hurt you.

01:16.416 --> 01:17.958
Do you understand?

01:20.041 --> 01:22.166
It's cold. We have blankets.

01:22.250 --> 01:24.708
Boy, you have your dog.
Girl, you have your kitty.

01:24.791 --> 01:28.625
This is just a place.
There's nothing more that we need from it.

01:28.708 --> 01:30.500
Do you understand?

01:32.583 --> 01:35.791
And no talking on the river.

01:37.125 --> 01:39.708
You must listen as closely as you can.

01:39.791 --> 01:42.541
If you hear something in the woods,
you tell me.

01:42.625 --> 01:45.250
If you hear something in the water,
you tell me.

01:45.333 --> 01:48.708
But you never, ever
take off your blindfold.

01:48.791 --> 01:51.000
If you look, you will die.

01:51.291 --> 01:52.541
Do you understand?

01:54.875 --> 01:55.958
[chirps]

01:56.666 --> 01:59.583
[Malorie whispers] It's okay.
It's okay. It's okay.

01:59.666 --> 02:02.333
-[Girl] Kitty.
-[Malorie] It's okay. It's okay.

02:03.333 --> 02:04.375
[Girl laughs]

02:05.958 --> 02:07.958
[chirping]

02:14.000 --> 02:14.833
Let's go.

02:23.583 --> 02:25.250
[Malorie panting]

02:30.000 --> 02:31.458
[Malorie whispering] Okay. Okay.

02:31.541 --> 02:35.833
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

02:36.416 --> 02:38.791
-Ah.
-[distorted voices speaking]

02:44.000 --> 02:45.375
[Malorie panting]

02:48.250 --> 02:51.708
[whispering] Twenty-eight, 29, 30.
Okay, this way. It's fine.

02:52.625 --> 02:54.250
Thirty-one, 32, 33.

02:54.333 --> 02:55.708
Where is it? Where is it?

02:58.458 --> 02:59.291
[Malorie grunts]

03:01.166 --> 03:03.208
[Malorie panting]

03:05.708 --> 03:07.208
[grunts]

03:29.333 --> 03:30.666
[pants]

03:33.791 --> 03:36.125
["Coming Down" playing]

03:37.916 --> 03:39.250
♪ Whoa ♪

03:40.375 --> 03:44.458
♪ I take as much ♪

03:44.541 --> 03:47.291
♪ As I can get ♪

03:50.875 --> 03:55.208
♪ I don't take ♪

03:55.291 --> 03:58.875
♪ Any regret ♪

04:01.291 --> 04:05.916
♪ I think I'm com-- ♪

04:06.000 --> 04:07.083
[music stops]

04:07.708 --> 04:11.625
-Uh... asshole, I was listening to that.
-Yeah, so were the people down the street.

04:11.708 --> 04:14.541
The store was packed.
This thing seems serious.

04:14.625 --> 04:16.625
Wow, you literally have no food.

04:16.708 --> 04:18.708
-What-- What thing?
-Are you serious?

04:18.791 --> 04:20.583
-I'm serious.
-Turn on the news, dumb-dumb.

04:20.666 --> 04:21.916
[scoffs] Dumb-dumb.

04:22.500 --> 04:24.791
-What channel, dumb-dumb?
-Any one of them.

04:24.875 --> 04:27.458
[reporter] Airports and train stations
have shut down.

04:27.541 --> 04:31.541
Streets are crowded with people
escaping cities by car and on foot

04:31.625 --> 04:35.125
as witnesses report
unexplained mass suicides.

04:35.208 --> 04:37.125
First recorded in Romania,

04:37.208 --> 04:40.541
there's now an alarming spread
of incidents into Europe and Siberia.

04:40.625 --> 04:43.750
Estimated death toll
is in the tens of thousands.

04:43.833 --> 04:47.625
...don't yet know what is causing
the mass suicides in Europe and Russia.

04:47.708 --> 04:51.291
The eyewitness reports tell of people
exhibiting psychotic behavior.

04:51.375 --> 04:52.958
Our sources are telling us

04:53.041 --> 04:55.583
this does not appear to be
pathological or viral.

04:55.666 --> 04:58.375
US authorities are advising the public
to remain calm.

04:59.000 --> 05:00.791
There have been
no officially confirmed inst--

05:01.375 --> 05:02.708
Well, it's in Russia, so...

05:03.375 --> 05:06.708
Well, try telling that to the soccer moms
fighting over bottled water.

05:06.791 --> 05:10.208
Speaking of which,
I just got off the phone with Mom.

05:10.291 --> 05:12.625
How come I have to update her
about you all the time?

05:12.708 --> 05:15.375
-Why do you have to talk about me?
-I'm not telling her about my life.

05:16.958 --> 05:20.041
At three o'clock, I'm gonna go check out
an Arabian stud in Sausalito.

05:20.125 --> 05:22.291
See, now that is a sentence
you don't hear every day.

05:22.375 --> 05:26.250
-You wanna come?
-I can't. I've got my OB with Dr. Lapham.

05:26.333 --> 05:27.791
-Lapham, when?
-Oh, my God.

05:27.875 --> 05:29.791
Why does your voice get high
when it gets excited?

05:29.875 --> 05:31.416
-How about I drive you?
-No, I'm fine.

05:31.500 --> 05:33.666
I can go in. We can maybe see the baby.

05:33.750 --> 05:36.333
Or I can cancel the appointment
and we can go and see a horse.

05:36.416 --> 05:38.125
No. Fuck the horse.

05:38.208 --> 05:40.166
Wow. Such venom.

05:42.125 --> 05:43.500
What do you think?

05:45.458 --> 05:49.208
I think I see
a whole bunch of people sitting together,

05:49.291 --> 05:51.125
but they all feel incredibly lonely.

05:51.208 --> 05:52.833
The loneliness is just incidental.

05:53.416 --> 05:55.958
It's really about
people's inability to connect.

05:59.125 --> 06:00.583
Inability to connect to what?

06:00.666 --> 06:01.875
-Can you move?
-Malorie.

06:01.958 --> 06:03.625
-I need you to move.
-We've been through this.

06:03.708 --> 06:05.916
-Mm-hmm.
-That's not how it's gonna be for you.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.708
It's different with a baby.
It's an immediate love affair.

06:09.791 --> 06:11.708
-It's not gonna be that way for me.
-Yes, it will.

06:11.791 --> 06:13.958
-No, ma'am.
-You should be afraid of being alone,

06:14.041 --> 06:15.208
not of this.

06:17.041 --> 06:20.000
And what we need to do is get you...
[clicks tongue]

06:20.083 --> 06:22.500
...out into the real world
with other people,

06:22.583 --> 06:24.500
not stuck in this house all day.
You never leave.

06:24.583 --> 06:26.875
Why should I leave?
I have you to get me groceries.

06:26.958 --> 06:28.291
-You have to move.
-No, not moving.

06:28.375 --> 06:29.541
-Yes, you do.
-Not moving.

06:29.625 --> 06:31.250
-Why?
-Not moving. I love my house!

06:31.333 --> 06:33.791
I know it took you a long time
to find a studio you loved,

06:33.875 --> 06:36.291
and ever since Ryan left,
you've gotten a lot more work done.

06:36.375 --> 06:38.875
But, so fine, so no more roommates.

06:38.958 --> 06:40.041
Ryan was not a roommate.

06:40.125 --> 06:41.833
Uh, it turns out he kind of was.

06:44.833 --> 06:48.541
Anyway, can't raise a kid here.
Where would you even put her?

06:49.666 --> 06:51.125
How do you know it's a she?

06:52.291 --> 06:53.916
Wishful thinking, I guess.

06:56.583 --> 06:57.875
[cell phone ringing]

06:59.333 --> 07:01.416
[Jessica] Sorry, it's work.
I'll be there in a second.

07:01.500 --> 07:02.833
[woman speaking over PA]

07:02.916 --> 07:03.833
Hi.

07:03.916 --> 07:06.791
[man] Yeah, they just had
to push the surgery back an hour.

07:06.875 --> 07:07.708
[woman] Yes?

07:11.125 --> 07:12.000
Yeah.

07:12.083 --> 07:13.750
I'll call right back.

07:13.833 --> 07:14.708
What?

07:15.708 --> 07:17.458
You still don't wanna know the gender?

07:17.541 --> 07:20.166
And ruin the surprise, Dr. Lapham? No.

07:21.250 --> 07:24.833
[Dr. Lapham] How have you been feeling?
Have you been sleeping any better?

07:24.916 --> 07:25.833
[Malorie] Rough.

07:25.916 --> 07:28.666
I never slept well
before I had this condition.

07:28.750 --> 07:31.125
It's called pregnancy.
It's okay to say it out loud.

07:31.208 --> 07:33.791
Oh, don't you know, Doctor,
if you don't acknowledge a thing,

07:33.875 --> 07:34.833
it simply goes away?

07:34.916 --> 07:37.166
Oh, really? All this time, I had no idea.

07:37.250 --> 07:39.041
-[Jessica] When a horse gets pregnant...
-God, the horse.

07:39.125 --> 07:42.958
You know about horses? When a horse
gets pregnant, it knows right away.

07:43.041 --> 07:43.916
Does it?

07:44.000 --> 07:46.208
It changes the way it eats.
It changes its gait.

07:46.291 --> 07:49.041
It bites all the other horses
who come too close.

07:49.125 --> 07:50.500
It's too bad we're not horses.

07:50.583 --> 07:53.791
It is too bad. Great to be a horse.
Then we would have, like, a mother

07:53.875 --> 07:55.458
who would have actually raised us

07:55.541 --> 07:58.416
and a father
off on some faraway stud farm.

07:58.500 --> 08:00.916
Hold on.
Our father was off on a faraway stud farm.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.541
-That is correct. [chuckles]
-[Malorie] That is correct.

08:04.583 --> 08:05.750
Poor us.

08:05.833 --> 08:09.375
We should go feel sorry for ourselves
with lunch and a bottle of wine.

08:09.458 --> 08:11.583
Oh, finally,
now you're making some sense.

08:11.666 --> 08:13.750
-Good.
-Really, in front of me?

08:13.833 --> 08:14.833
We didn't mean it...

08:14.916 --> 08:17.791
No, like a tiny glass of rosé
is not gonna hurt the little bean.

08:17.875 --> 08:19.541
I'm pretty sure I heard the word "bottle."

08:19.625 --> 08:21.750
You might want to think of a name
besides "little bean"

08:21.833 --> 08:24.125
seeing as your child
is now the size of a small melon.

08:25.083 --> 08:26.083
[both] Small melon!

08:26.166 --> 08:29.000
I know it's hard to love someone
you haven't met yet.

08:29.583 --> 08:31.041
Oh, that's beautiful.

08:32.083 --> 08:35.458
Thought about stitching that on,
like, a little lavender sachet?

08:36.041 --> 08:38.125
-Could sell them in the gift shop.
-In the gift shop.

08:38.208 --> 08:39.583
You're having a baby, Malorie.

08:40.166 --> 08:44.708
Pretty soon you and I, Jessica,
and some hard-ass labor and delivery nurse

08:44.791 --> 08:46.875
will be on the third floor
making the same wise cracks.

08:46.958 --> 08:49.583
Only this time,
you won't be going home by yourself.

08:50.708 --> 08:52.375
I know. I know.

08:54.375 --> 08:56.625
[Dr. Lapham]
But if that's not what you want,

08:56.708 --> 08:59.500
there are plenty of couples
who are desperate to adopt a child.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.750
There are no judgments here.
You can make whatever choice you want.

09:02.833 --> 09:06.666
But what you can't do is ignore it
and hope it just goes away.

09:12.083 --> 09:13.708
[gagging]

09:15.833 --> 09:16.958
[spits]

09:17.958 --> 09:19.500
[knock on door]

09:20.333 --> 09:21.958
[Jessica] You okay in there?

09:22.041 --> 09:23.125
[Malorie] I'm great.

09:24.208 --> 09:25.083
Are you puking?

09:26.833 --> 09:27.833
Just go to the car.

09:27.916 --> 09:29.125
Is it chunky?

09:29.208 --> 09:33.250
No, it was actually the really smooth kind
that just shoots out real clean.

09:33.333 --> 09:35.125
I'll meet you at the car, okay?

09:36.416 --> 09:38.791
-[man] In the corridor.
-[woman] Let's get it clear.

09:53.666 --> 09:56.041
[thudding]

09:56.125 --> 09:58.500
[woman] Hey! Hey! Hey, security!

09:58.583 --> 10:00.041
Watch out. Help. I need help!

10:00.125 --> 10:02.291
[indistinct shouting]

10:02.375 --> 10:03.500
No, get back!

10:03.583 --> 10:06.333
-Calm down. Please calm down.
-Code gray. Level one.

10:06.416 --> 10:08.250
Calm down. Security!

10:18.333 --> 10:20.750
-[Jessica] You feel better?
-It's happening now.

10:20.833 --> 10:21.708
You get any on you?

10:21.791 --> 10:24.375
The thing in Russia that's making
everybody crazy, it's here now.

10:24.458 --> 10:26.208
-What?
-Can you just, please--

10:26.291 --> 10:27.875
-[tires squeal]
-[indistinct shouting]

10:27.958 --> 10:29.958
-[man] Hold on.
-[woman] Inside the hospital.

10:30.041 --> 10:31.125
Go, go, go, go!

10:36.958 --> 10:37.791
[tires screech]

10:38.375 --> 10:39.666
Go, go, go, go, go!

10:39.750 --> 10:42.541
[police siren blaring]

10:45.875 --> 10:47.333
We're going straight to Santa Rosa.

10:47.416 --> 10:49.958
You can stay at my place
until whatever the fuck this is isn't.

10:50.041 --> 10:52.333
-I don't have any clothes.
-You can wear something of mine.

10:52.416 --> 10:54.333
I'm not much of a chaps-and-boots gal.

10:54.416 --> 10:56.291
You're worried about
what to wear right now?

10:56.375 --> 10:58.583
Well, I find it comforting
to focus on the wrong things.

10:59.250 --> 11:01.083
-[Jessica] Shit.
-[Malorie] What?

11:01.166 --> 11:03.333
There's a car stopped in
the middle of the fucking road.

11:03.416 --> 11:04.291
Stop. Just go round.

11:04.375 --> 11:05.375
[Jessica] Move. Let me go.

11:05.458 --> 11:07.833
If this thing gets any worse,
you'll wanna be off the roads

11:07.916 --> 11:10.125
-and on a damn horse, trust me.
-[horn honks]

11:14.333 --> 11:16.500
-[Jessica] Oh, my God!
-Shit. Shit, shit, shit!

11:16.583 --> 11:18.708
People have to stop being so stupid.

11:20.625 --> 11:22.375
Oh, my God, Jess. Just go. Go.

11:22.458 --> 11:24.291
I'm not running the light
with a pregnant lady in the car.

11:24.375 --> 11:25.625
Just drive the car!

11:25.708 --> 11:27.750
You gotta let me just drive.
You're freaking me out.

11:27.833 --> 11:30.000
-[Malorie] You know what?
-Just let me do it.

11:32.708 --> 11:34.541
[cell phone ringing]

11:34.625 --> 11:37.250
-This isn't me.
-My phone is in the back seat.

11:37.333 --> 11:40.125
-It's the foreman wondering where I am.
-Right, just hold your horses.

11:40.208 --> 11:42.083
-[Jessica] Yeah, ha ha.
-What did you do with it?

11:42.166 --> 11:45.250
-Oh, my God. What the fuck is that?
-[rumbling]

11:45.333 --> 11:46.583
-[growl]
-What the fuck is what?

11:46.666 --> 11:48.333
[people screaming]

11:48.416 --> 11:49.583
What the fuck is what?

11:49.666 --> 11:50.791
[Jessica panting]

11:50.875 --> 11:52.708
What the fuck is what?
What are you looking at?

11:52.791 --> 11:55.041
What did you see? Talk to me.
What the fuck is what?

11:55.125 --> 11:57.541
What are you doing? Oh, my God, Jess.
Jess, don't do that.

11:57.625 --> 12:01.416
Just what are you-- What is wrong
with you? No. Stop it! Stop it!

12:01.500 --> 12:03.000
No, no, no!

12:03.083 --> 12:04.083
Stop it! Stop it!

12:04.166 --> 12:07.833
Jess, what the fuck is wrong with you?
Jess, please. Stop it, Jess.

12:07.916 --> 12:10.166
God damn it! Stop it! Please stop it!

12:26.541 --> 12:28.541
[people screaming]

12:32.708 --> 12:34.958
[horn honks]

12:38.625 --> 12:39.791
[groans]

12:49.333 --> 12:51.416
[horn honks]

13:07.583 --> 13:09.166
[tires squeal]

13:11.166 --> 13:12.708
[screaming]

13:19.208 --> 13:21.416
[distorted voice]

13:27.833 --> 13:29.500
-Lydia, what are you doing?
-She's pregnant.

13:29.583 --> 13:31.750
Lydia, not now. Let's go in.

13:31.833 --> 13:33.083
She's pregnant.

13:33.166 --> 13:34.208
You can't help!

13:34.291 --> 13:35.791
-[siren blaring]
-[horn honks]

13:36.458 --> 13:38.333
Hurry, come inside!

13:38.416 --> 13:39.333
Okay.

13:41.541 --> 13:42.875
[grunts]

13:42.958 --> 13:44.666
Sweetheart, get up. Right now.

13:46.333 --> 13:47.291
Mom.

13:48.291 --> 13:49.208
Please don't go.

13:51.125 --> 13:52.000
Please don't go.

13:52.083 --> 13:53.583
[distorted voice whispers]

14:02.041 --> 14:03.958
[man] Hey. Hey. Hey.

14:05.333 --> 14:06.833
Keep your eyes down.

14:28.208 --> 14:29.125
[pounding on door]

14:29.208 --> 14:31.250
[Tom] Open the door.
This woman is pregnant.

14:31.333 --> 14:33.291
-Open the door!
-No.

14:34.125 --> 14:37.208
-[Lucy] Hey! Open the door. Police.
-[Douglas] Don't open it.

14:37.291 --> 14:40.541
-[Lucy] Police! Open the fucking door!
-I'm sorry. It's my house.

14:41.208 --> 14:42.583
Get in. Hurry!

14:42.666 --> 14:44.666
Come on. You good?

14:46.708 --> 14:47.750
Are you okay?

14:47.833 --> 14:49.833
[Malorie panting]

14:55.000 --> 14:56.416
She went to help you.

14:58.666 --> 14:59.833
Now she's gone.

15:01.541 --> 15:04.375
[Greg] Come on. Now everybody's
obviously just a little freaked out.

15:04.458 --> 15:07.083
-I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.
-[Greg] Come in. Come inside the house.

15:08.250 --> 15:09.833
[Greg whispers] Come on. Come on.

15:14.041 --> 15:15.625
[Greg] Is everybody all right?

15:15.708 --> 15:18.541
Is anyone getting service in here?
You don't have any Wi-Fi?

15:18.625 --> 15:19.791
[Greg] I have not gotten any.

15:19.875 --> 15:21.250
[woman] Come on.

15:21.333 --> 15:23.583
-It's not working.
-[Jason] I gotta get a hold of my kids.

15:23.666 --> 15:25.250
-No, nothing.
-[busy signal]

15:25.333 --> 15:27.541
-[man] Honey?
-[woman] Nothing. I have nothing.

15:28.500 --> 15:30.125
-[man] They're at home?
-Excuse me.

15:30.208 --> 15:31.375
[line ringing]

15:33.875 --> 15:36.958
Mom? Mom, call me. Call me right now.

15:37.041 --> 15:39.875
Something... [sniffles] Hello? Hello?

15:39.958 --> 15:41.166
[phone beeps]

15:42.500 --> 15:46.208
That thing fucks with your nervous system.
I've seen it in my clients for weeks.

15:46.291 --> 15:48.333
Hey, did I mention I'm a fucking cop?

15:50.125 --> 15:51.958
You're in the Academy.
Doesn't make you a cop.

15:52.041 --> 15:55.666
Whatever it is,
I'm sure they'll send someone soon.

15:55.750 --> 15:59.666
No, the only thing that will happen soon
is we're all gonna die soon.

16:00.250 --> 16:03.750
This has a classic bio-warfare signature.

16:03.833 --> 16:05.583
North Korea or Iran.

16:05.666 --> 16:08.541
[Greg] Douglas, that's it.
They don't know what it is yet, okay?

16:08.625 --> 16:10.666
We just all gotta try to stay calm.

16:10.750 --> 16:12.041
-Really?
-[Lucy] Yeah.

16:12.625 --> 16:13.666
[Greg] Please.

16:15.666 --> 16:17.166
We are so fucking fucked.

16:17.750 --> 16:19.250
[Cheryl] I think I heard one.

16:19.833 --> 16:24.291
We were running up the street,
and I swear to God, I-- I felt something.

16:24.375 --> 16:26.583
-I heard something.
-[Lucy] Did you see it? What was it?

16:26.666 --> 16:29.458
-I-- I don't know. It was just there.
-[busy signal]

16:29.541 --> 16:31.208
-[Lucy] The presence?
-[Cheryl] Yeah.

16:31.791 --> 16:33.000
So fucking fucked.

16:33.083 --> 16:34.916
[distorted growl]

16:39.875 --> 16:42.666
[Lucy] Gotta be an image out there.
They must have released some video.

16:42.750 --> 16:45.416
-I haven't seen anything.
-[Tom] My crew saw one.

16:45.500 --> 16:46.375
-What?
-What?

16:46.458 --> 16:49.000
One minute,
we were digging a foundation...

16:49.666 --> 16:52.541
and then my contractor just lies down
in front of the bulldozer.

16:52.625 --> 16:56.500
And then my operator tips the rig
into the ditch and snaps his own neck.

16:56.583 --> 16:59.750
-[Cheryl] Oh.
-[Greg] It seems like if you look at it,

16:59.833 --> 17:03.458
it makes you crazy
or it makes you wanna hurt yourself.

17:04.041 --> 17:06.083
No, it makes you kill yourself.

17:06.666 --> 17:09.666
[Cheryl] And you just...
you just look at it.

17:09.750 --> 17:12.541
-[Lucy] And you commit suicide.
-[man] How can that be?

17:12.625 --> 17:15.375
Close the windows. Get the windows!
Close all the windows.

17:18.083 --> 17:21.291
-Everybody, get the windows.
-[busy signal]

17:25.166 --> 17:27.208
[busy signal]

17:27.291 --> 17:28.875
[phone ringing]

17:28.958 --> 17:30.291
Oh, thank you, Jesus.

17:30.375 --> 17:31.833
Andy, Bailey, can you hear me?

17:31.916 --> 17:34.708
-[Bailey] Dad? What's that thing outside?
-[static]

17:34.791 --> 17:36.625
-Bailey! Bailey?
-Bailey.

17:36.708 --> 17:39.708
-[Bailey screams]
-Bailey! Bailey!

17:39.791 --> 17:42.250
-If you go outside, you'll die.
-My children are out there!

17:42.333 --> 17:44.625
-[Jason] Move!
-You won't make it to your children!

17:44.708 --> 17:48.000
-[Felix] It's back on. Turn it up.
-[reporter] The President has declared

17:48.083 --> 17:50.375
a state of emergency
and has closed all borders.

17:51.208 --> 17:53.541
Do not, do not go outside.

17:53.625 --> 17:55.666
-Avoid social media. Use radi--
-[gunshot]

17:56.458 --> 17:58.083
[static]

17:58.166 --> 18:00.500
What? What in the shit is happening?

18:00.583 --> 18:03.708
-It's an end game, man.
-[Cheryl] I'm sorry, what?

18:03.791 --> 18:07.250
The end game. Humanity has been judged,
and we've been found wanting.

18:07.833 --> 18:10.291
-[Lucy] Judged? By who?
-[Charlie] They go by different names.

18:10.958 --> 18:14.500
You got world religion and mythology
that's full of mentions of demons

18:14.583 --> 18:17.250
or spirit creatures.
People who've seen these creatures

18:17.333 --> 18:19.875
almost always describe
their encounter as this...

18:19.958 --> 18:23.208
as with an entity that takes on
a form of your worst fears or...

18:23.833 --> 18:25.833
your deepest sadness
or your greatest loss.

18:25.916 --> 18:27.833
Sounds like bullshit to me.
Religious talk.

18:27.916 --> 18:31.125
It's not bullshit, okay?
It's real talk. It's facts.

18:31.208 --> 18:32.791
They come in all different forms.

18:32.875 --> 18:37.833
You got the Aka Manah, the Varios Daevas
from ancient Zoroastrian legend.

18:37.916 --> 18:41.083
You've got the Surgat
from ancient Christian occult beliefs

18:41.166 --> 18:45.166
that made pregnant women encounter
their unborn children as other creatures

18:45.250 --> 18:46.708
such as lobsters or spiders.

18:46.791 --> 18:51.291
You've got the Huli-jing from China.
You've got the Puca from Celtic mythology.

18:51.375 --> 18:54.583
All different names, but the same thing.

18:54.666 --> 18:55.666
And what's that?

18:57.625 --> 18:58.750
The end of us.

18:59.541 --> 19:02.625
Charlie, did you learn all of that
working at the supermarket?

19:03.791 --> 19:06.916
-No, I've been studying it for years.
-In college?

19:07.000 --> 19:09.375
Not college per se, but...

19:09.458 --> 19:12.333
I mean the Internet. That's where you get
all your information from.

19:12.416 --> 19:15.208
-I'm working on a novel, guys.
-Fuck's sake.

19:15.291 --> 19:18.083
[Felix] So we can't do anything
but wait here until we go crazy like him?

19:18.166 --> 19:21.166
[Cheryl] The army is bound
to get this under control.

19:21.250 --> 19:23.041
We just have to wait.

19:23.791 --> 19:27.250
[Tom] Hey. Hey.
Why don't we sit back down?

19:27.333 --> 19:30.083
No, no, no. I'm fine.
I'm-- I'm just trying to make a call.

19:30.166 --> 19:31.666
-Understood.
-[Malorie] I'm okay.

19:31.750 --> 19:33.583
Understood. Understood. Um...

19:34.333 --> 19:36.875
-The phones aren't working right now.
-Okay. Okay.

19:37.791 --> 19:40.333
[Tom] Listen, are you in any pain?

19:42.000 --> 19:43.083
What? No. No.

19:43.166 --> 19:46.000
-I feel like you may have a concussion.
-I am fine. I'm fine.

19:46.083 --> 19:47.250
-Okay. Okay.
-I am fine.

19:47.833 --> 19:48.750
Okay.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.250
We were just driving.

19:59.416 --> 20:00.875
And then she saw something.

20:01.458 --> 20:05.750
I didn't see what it was,
but then she got this look on her face.

20:05.833 --> 20:07.166
[sighs]

20:13.458 --> 20:14.708
[sniffles]

20:16.458 --> 20:18.041
[weeping] It's like she got--

20:24.375 --> 20:28.416
She got so sad, and Jess does not get sad.

20:29.000 --> 20:30.041
No.

20:31.250 --> 20:34.250
She stepped out of the car
and ran into the street...

20:34.833 --> 20:36.750
and she's not suicidal. [sniffles]

20:36.833 --> 20:38.166
She would never do that.

20:39.791 --> 20:41.208
But it was...

20:41.291 --> 20:44.458
And then that woman--
that woman, she saw me,

20:44.541 --> 20:48.166
and then she started talking
to her mom and I...

20:48.250 --> 20:49.541
[sniffles]

20:49.625 --> 20:51.750
[Douglas] That woman was my wife.

20:52.333 --> 20:54.166
-Her name was Lydia.
-[Malorie] Okay.

20:54.708 --> 20:58.458
And she wasn't talking to her mother.
Her mother's been dead ten years.

21:07.666 --> 21:09.333
[wind whistles]

21:12.625 --> 21:14.375
[growl]

21:15.125 --> 21:17.125
[distorted whispering]

22:03.041 --> 22:04.375
[sighs]

22:06.250 --> 22:07.708
[chirping]

22:16.791 --> 22:17.833
[beeps]

22:18.916 --> 22:19.791
Hello?

22:20.916 --> 22:22.750
Hello, can anybody hear me? Hello?

22:22.833 --> 22:24.125
[static]

22:27.833 --> 22:29.541
Hello? Can anybody hear me? Hello.

22:31.458 --> 22:33.833
Is anybody out there?
Hello, my name is Malorie.

22:33.916 --> 22:35.875
I'm on the river. Is anybody out there?

22:36.708 --> 22:38.666
Hello? Hello? Is anybody out there?

22:40.541 --> 22:42.458
Can anybody hear me? Hello?

22:42.541 --> 22:43.708
[static]

22:46.250 --> 22:47.541
[birds chirp]

22:52.125 --> 22:54.708
[distorted whispers] Malorie. Malorie.

22:57.583 --> 22:59.250
[wind whistles]

22:59.958 --> 23:01.541
-Malorie.
-[growl]

23:09.708 --> 23:14.208
[man over radio] It's been three days
since these, um, events unfolded.

23:14.291 --> 23:15.708
Station's lines are down.

23:15.791 --> 23:17.916
I can't get in touch with anyone.

23:18.000 --> 23:20.666
We haven't heard anything
from any authorities...

23:20.750 --> 23:22.000
but if you are listening,

23:22.083 --> 23:25.000
from what I can gather,
as long as you stay indoors,

23:25.083 --> 23:28.250
as long as you don't look
at those things...

23:29.083 --> 23:30.500
you should be fine.

23:30.583 --> 23:32.333
Do not go outside.

23:32.416 --> 23:36.666
The moment I receive any more news,
I will be sure to update you.

23:36.750 --> 23:40.833
My husband works in trusts and estates.
What kind of law do you practice?

23:40.916 --> 23:43.791
-Bankruptcy.
-When he's not suing his neighbors.

23:44.291 --> 23:46.083
[Felix] Hey, how long's
our food gonna last?

23:46.166 --> 23:47.583
[Douglas] Not much longer.

23:47.666 --> 23:50.875
Because some of us
don't understand the concept of rationing.

23:51.541 --> 23:53.208
Douglas, your house is behind this one.

23:53.291 --> 23:55.125
When we finish this,
let's go for a food run.

23:55.208 --> 23:57.583
We'd never make it back.
What you don't understand is--

23:57.666 --> 23:59.166
[knocking on door]

24:04.916 --> 24:07.041
-[Lucy] Hey, Tom...
-We can't let anyone in.

24:07.125 --> 24:08.958
Okay, just calm down.

24:11.375 --> 24:14.000
-[Tom] Hello?
-[woman] Yes, hello.

24:14.083 --> 24:15.750
-You're making a big mistake.
-Douglas.

24:15.833 --> 24:17.666
-[Tom] Yes, hello.
-[woman] Hello?

24:18.541 --> 24:21.500
[crying] My name is Olympia.
I need help. Please.

24:21.583 --> 24:23.833
-Don't open the goddamn--
-I'm gonna open the door.

24:23.916 --> 24:24.791
[Douglas] Fuck!

24:25.291 --> 24:26.416
[Tom] Okay, one second.

24:27.708 --> 24:29.083
Hey! Hey, hey, hey, hey.

24:31.166 --> 24:32.208
Move.

24:36.125 --> 24:37.125
Go ahead.

24:38.458 --> 24:39.625
[Malorie] Go ahead.

24:39.708 --> 24:41.916
Go get a--
Go get a blanket. Go get a blanket.

24:43.708 --> 24:45.541
There should be two lamps
on either side of the door.

24:45.625 --> 24:49.041
I'm gonna hand you a blanket and I want
you to drape it across the both of them.

24:49.125 --> 24:50.208
-[Olympia] Okay.
-Okay?

24:50.291 --> 24:52.000
I need you to block the view for me.

24:52.083 --> 24:53.583
-Cover your eyes.
-[Felix] So stupid.

24:54.166 --> 24:55.750
[Tom] Malorie, cover your eyes.

25:00.708 --> 25:01.791
[Tom] Here. Here. Okay.

25:02.625 --> 25:03.666
[Olympia] Okay.

25:03.750 --> 25:04.583
[door closes]

25:04.666 --> 25:06.333
[Tom] Let me know when you have it.

25:10.875 --> 25:11.791
Tom, is this safe?

25:11.875 --> 25:13.791
-Shut up.
-[Tom] Hold on, please!

25:14.291 --> 25:16.833
-[Olympia] Okay, it's all covered.
-[Tom] Okay.

25:16.916 --> 25:18.791
-I got you. Come on.
-[door opens]

25:18.875 --> 25:19.875
Hold on. Hold on.

25:20.541 --> 25:21.750
[Olympia panting]

25:21.833 --> 25:23.291
-[Tom] We're good.
-[door closes]

25:23.375 --> 25:24.250
[lock clicks]

25:24.958 --> 25:26.625
-Malorie.
-[Malorie] Yeah.

25:26.708 --> 25:28.250
-The gun, please.
-Yeah.

25:28.333 --> 25:31.833
Yeah, before you kill someone with it
since you have no idea how it works.

25:36.791 --> 25:38.333
-[panting]
-[Greg] It's okay.

25:43.541 --> 25:44.583
How...

25:45.125 --> 25:46.541
There are so many of you.

25:46.625 --> 25:48.208
So are you, um...

25:49.458 --> 25:50.833
Are-- Are you pregnant?

25:51.958 --> 25:54.083
Yeah. October 1st.

25:55.875 --> 25:56.791
What about you?

25:59.500 --> 26:01.583
Uh, end of, uh, September.

26:01.666 --> 26:04.416
[Felix] Wait. Hold on. Is shit
still going crazy out there or what?

26:05.083 --> 26:06.750
[Cheryl] Are you on your own?

26:06.833 --> 26:08.333
Yeah, I am.

26:08.416 --> 26:11.833
My husband was deployed last month
'cause he's in the Air Force.

26:11.916 --> 26:14.541
I tried to make stuff last
as long as I could, um...

26:15.166 --> 26:18.458
but I was so hungry
and I was afraid I would starve my baby,

26:18.541 --> 26:19.875
so I didn't know what to do.

26:19.958 --> 26:21.416
-[Tom] Have some water.
-Thank you.

26:21.500 --> 26:24.000
So you left and started knocking
on random doors?

26:24.083 --> 26:25.708
[Olympia] I only live a block away.

26:25.791 --> 26:29.000
Great, now we can all starve
here in the maternity ward.

26:30.333 --> 26:32.500
It just means we need
to get more supplies.

26:32.583 --> 26:34.958
Of course, but we can't get anything
if we can't see.

26:35.041 --> 26:36.708
Oh, we're so fucking trapped.

26:37.291 --> 26:38.291
Maybe not.

26:39.750 --> 26:41.375
Maybe we can see better than we thought.

26:43.000 --> 26:45.416
-[Malorie] What do you mean?
-[Greg] Come here.

26:48.208 --> 26:51.083
We have cameras around the house
transmitting a live feed.

26:51.750 --> 26:53.250
Come upstairs. Come on.

26:58.333 --> 26:59.791
[Greg] It's a digitized signal.

26:59.875 --> 27:03.458
It just shows the color temperatures
of the objects. It's neutered information.

27:03.541 --> 27:06.208
-Colors on a flat screen.
-But an image can still have power.

27:06.291 --> 27:08.250
We have no idea
how these things can operate.

27:08.333 --> 27:09.875
These images are not direct.

27:10.916 --> 27:13.083
We can't look at whatever it is
with the naked eye,

27:13.166 --> 27:15.291
but maybe we can with a translator.

27:16.291 --> 27:17.166
Pixels and heat.

27:17.250 --> 27:18.375
Maybe it won't even show up.

27:18.458 --> 27:22.458
Well, we're not gonna find out
until one of us takes a look.

27:23.583 --> 27:25.208
I think it's a huge mistake.

27:25.291 --> 27:28.083
You would, Douglas.
You think everything is a huge mistake.

27:28.666 --> 27:30.625
Sooner or later
we're gonna have to do something.

27:30.708 --> 27:32.833
We don't know how long
we're gonna have electricity.

27:32.916 --> 27:35.708
You gotta trust me on this.
I really think this is gonna work.

27:36.250 --> 27:38.041
Okay. Okay.

27:38.125 --> 27:41.166
Maybe if it does, we could use
the technology for supply runs or---

27:41.250 --> 27:42.166
[Greg] Exactly.

27:42.250 --> 27:43.833
[Greg] Just not too tight.

27:43.916 --> 27:45.625
I hope you know what you're doing.

27:45.708 --> 27:51.416
Listen... you and your husband,
you're good people.

27:51.500 --> 27:54.875
You know, it wasn't... It wasn't that.

27:55.791 --> 27:57.125
Thank you, Douglas.

27:57.208 --> 27:58.291
[grunts]

27:59.875 --> 28:01.291
You don't have to do this.

28:01.875 --> 28:03.791
I know. Don't worry.

28:05.958 --> 28:08.583
-Tom, I need the remote.
-Yeah.

28:08.666 --> 28:09.833
There you go, bud.

28:19.000 --> 28:20.000
[computer beeps]

28:40.333 --> 28:41.583
So why are you suing him?

28:41.666 --> 28:43.708
'Cause they want to tear down
this part of their house

28:43.791 --> 28:46.000
and build some glass monstrosity.

28:46.083 --> 28:47.750
His husband's an architect.

28:47.833 --> 28:51.333
It's his property.
Why do you care what he builds?

28:52.625 --> 28:54.333
Because I have to look at it.

29:17.208 --> 29:18.458
[exhales]

29:20.583 --> 29:21.583
[Felix sniffles]

29:23.500 --> 29:25.000
Not a chance.

29:27.083 --> 29:30.250
Well, the world's ending, baby,
so you never know.

29:31.375 --> 29:33.583
-[scoffs]
-Hmm.

29:38.583 --> 29:40.458
[Greg] Where are you, motherfucker?

30:08.000 --> 30:09.250
[sighs]

30:16.000 --> 30:17.041
[inhales]

30:17.125 --> 30:18.250
Come on, Greg.

30:20.458 --> 30:21.333
Focus.

30:34.416 --> 30:37.375
It's, uh...
It's about the end of the world.

30:38.291 --> 30:39.375
My novel.

30:40.250 --> 30:43.583
But it's not one of those kids' stories
where they all got crossbows

30:43.666 --> 30:46.958
and they're killing each other to survive
or running around some giant maze.

30:47.041 --> 30:49.583
-[Malorie] Mm-hmm.
-No, this story is, um...

30:50.541 --> 30:51.750
This story's gonna be real.

30:52.333 --> 30:55.041
Did you ever think
it was gonna be anything like this?

31:02.083 --> 31:04.083
[rumble]

31:07.208 --> 31:09.291
[distorted whispering]

31:12.666 --> 31:14.250
[thudding]

31:16.958 --> 31:18.416
[thudding]

31:19.791 --> 31:21.916
[louder thudding]

31:23.958 --> 31:25.375
Greg! Greg, can we come in?

31:25.458 --> 31:26.875
-What's going on?
-Greg!

31:26.958 --> 31:28.625
[Malorie] Greg, can we come in?

31:30.083 --> 31:31.416
[Tom] Look away!

31:32.416 --> 31:34.708
Cover your eyes!
Cover your eyes. Find the monitor.

31:34.791 --> 31:36.291
-[Malorie] Greg.
-[Tom] Greg.

31:36.375 --> 31:37.750
-Come on, Greg.
-[Tom] Greg?

31:38.833 --> 31:41.041
-Shit.
-[Lucy] I've got it here.

31:43.083 --> 31:46.541
[Tom] Okay! Okay! Okay!
You can open your eyes. You can see.

31:46.625 --> 31:48.625
[Lucy panting]

31:52.125 --> 31:53.208
[sobs]

31:56.416 --> 31:58.625
I fucking told him that it was a mistake.

31:59.333 --> 32:02.333
[Tom] Come on.
We got to move. We got to move.

32:02.416 --> 32:06.791
-[weeping] I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.
-Come on. We gotta go.

32:07.625 --> 32:09.291
We're never getting out of here.

32:09.916 --> 32:11.916
[sobs] No one's coming for us.

32:12.000 --> 32:13.875
No one's coming for-- [gasps]

32:13.958 --> 32:15.916
-[sobs]
-We need to go.

32:20.791 --> 32:22.791
[wind blowing]

32:45.666 --> 32:47.708
[sighs]

32:50.625 --> 32:51.500
Hi.

32:52.125 --> 32:53.000
Hi.

32:53.083 --> 32:54.291
Yeah.

32:54.375 --> 32:57.333
I thought it might be good for us
to be close considering...

32:59.250 --> 33:00.125
Sure.

33:02.916 --> 33:05.208
[Olympia] You know,
this way, we won't be lonely.

33:05.291 --> 33:08.125
I read this blog post once
about how pregnant women

33:08.208 --> 33:10.000
should always sleep next to someone

33:10.083 --> 33:12.750
because the baby can sense
when the mother is lonely.

33:13.375 --> 33:14.458
Perfect.

33:16.041 --> 33:19.375
So, um...
have you thought about names yet?

33:20.541 --> 33:22.083
No, not yet.

33:23.291 --> 33:24.333
How about you?

33:25.458 --> 33:30.041
Well, if it's a girl we wanted
to name her, like, Ariel or Jasmine.

33:30.125 --> 33:34.333
I mean, I would love to name her
Cinderella and just call her Ella.

33:36.875 --> 33:39.500
And what did your husband like?

33:39.583 --> 33:41.291
He loves everything I love.

33:43.958 --> 33:46.500
What about you?
Does your husband have a favorite?

33:47.333 --> 33:48.541
Oh, it's just me.

33:49.458 --> 33:52.125
-Oh, I'm-- I'm sorry.
-No, it's fine. It's fine.

33:52.875 --> 33:54.916
Well, what about your family?
They must be excited--

33:55.000 --> 33:58.500
Do you know what?
Could you just excuse me for one second?

33:58.583 --> 33:59.625
I'll be right back.

34:04.833 --> 34:05.666
[sighs]

34:14.500 --> 34:16.083
[wind whistling]

34:16.166 --> 34:17.875
[rumbling]

34:17.958 --> 34:19.958
[distorted whispering]

34:27.458 --> 34:28.708
[creaking]

34:42.375 --> 34:44.375
[rumbling]

34:54.000 --> 34:55.000
Sorry.

34:58.125 --> 35:00.458
That's something you can't unsee.

35:01.791 --> 35:04.000
Ah, no. No, you cannot.

35:05.208 --> 35:06.083
Yeah.

35:08.250 --> 35:09.333
-[both chuckle]
-Sorry.

35:09.416 --> 35:10.291
Shh.

35:11.791 --> 35:13.583
-Shh, shh.
-Hmm.

35:19.208 --> 35:20.625
[whispering] Are you okay?

35:22.041 --> 35:23.166
Yeah.

35:24.458 --> 35:26.375
I'll wait to do my laundry in the morning.

35:27.458 --> 35:29.583
-That's probably a good idea.
-Yeah, I think so.

35:29.666 --> 35:30.791
Good night.

35:58.500 --> 35:59.666
[Malorie grunts]

36:02.583 --> 36:03.791
[Malorie grunts]

36:03.875 --> 36:05.291
[man] Hello!

36:06.708 --> 36:08.250
You guys need some help?

36:10.583 --> 36:14.250
-It's okay to take your blindfolds off.
-Do not take your blindfolds off. Do not!

36:15.458 --> 36:18.708
[man] I got some food.
Those kids look hungry.

36:18.791 --> 36:21.208
Get down! Get down! Get down!
Down. Down. Down.

36:29.791 --> 36:32.291
[man] Hey, little buddies.

36:33.083 --> 36:35.125
Have you ever seen a baby deer?

36:36.250 --> 36:37.708
I'll tell you a secret.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.208
I found one in the woods.

36:47.666 --> 36:51.083
Okay. I know you're scared.
Well, listen, there's no need.

36:56.375 --> 36:58.291
I'm not here to hurt you.
I can pull you to shore.

36:58.375 --> 37:00.500
[gunshots]

37:04.125 --> 37:06.458
[panting]

37:08.416 --> 37:10.875
-Take your goddamn blindfold off!
-[grunting]

37:11.458 --> 37:12.958
[man grunts]

37:13.041 --> 37:14.166
Ah!

37:14.250 --> 37:15.208
[Malorie grunts]

37:18.375 --> 37:20.125
[birds squawking]

37:20.208 --> 37:22.416
[man grunting]

37:23.958 --> 37:26.666
I've seen one. I've seen the truth.

37:26.750 --> 37:27.708
[Malorie grunting]

37:27.791 --> 37:29.833
Take your blindfold off.

37:29.916 --> 37:31.458
-[man laughing]
-[birds squawking]

37:31.541 --> 37:35.041
[man] It's beautiful. It's beautiful.
Take your blindfold off.

37:35.125 --> 37:36.833
[distorted growl]

37:36.916 --> 37:38.708
[grunting]

37:39.583 --> 37:41.541
[man] Take your blindfold off!

37:42.666 --> 37:44.166
[man screams]

37:44.250 --> 37:45.666
[Malorie grunting]

37:54.208 --> 37:57.333
[man] It shall cleanse the world!

37:57.416 --> 37:58.625
Everyone must look.

37:59.375 --> 38:01.208
Everyone must look.

38:11.833 --> 38:13.000
[Tom] Got some bad news.

38:14.458 --> 38:17.458
All right. We're running out of food
and there's no help coming.

38:17.541 --> 38:19.208
We've got to get outside.

38:22.333 --> 38:24.458
Look, I might know where we can get more.

38:25.458 --> 38:27.458
-Where, Charlie?
-The Fields market.

38:28.708 --> 38:31.125
I locked the place up
when everything started going crazy.

38:31.208 --> 38:34.666
-You're just telling us this?
-At least we know now. Thank you.

38:34.750 --> 38:37.250
Okay, so we'll need a group of us to go.

38:37.333 --> 38:39.125
Whoa. We'll be dead before we get there.

38:39.208 --> 38:40.833
-Are you kidding me?
-I'll go.

38:40.916 --> 38:43.166
-Well, if he's going, I'm going.
-You're pregnant!

38:43.250 --> 38:46.750
Well, if all you guys are going,
then I can come too.

38:46.833 --> 38:51.250
Why don't I go on the first run
and then you can go on the second run?

38:51.333 --> 38:52.625
-I'll come.
-[Felix] What?

38:52.708 --> 38:54.958
-It's a death wish.
-I have the training. It'll be fine.

38:55.041 --> 38:57.875
I don't like this.
I don't think anyone should go.

38:57.958 --> 39:00.375
-[Douglas] There are four of us.
-[Tom] Five. Charlie's going.

39:00.458 --> 39:02.750
Charlie's going?
Charlie ain't going nowhere.

39:02.833 --> 39:05.208
-You know the security system.
-No chance I'm going.

39:05.291 --> 39:07.208
I gave you the information.
That's all you needed.

39:07.291 --> 39:09.833
You don't need me to tell you
where to go. It is a supermarket.

39:09.916 --> 39:12.000
They got signs.
You've been shopping before.

39:12.083 --> 39:14.000
You wanna get cereal,
the sign will say cereals.

39:14.083 --> 39:15.958
If you can't read, I get it,
but you can read.

39:16.625 --> 39:20.791
-No. You don't need me to go with you--
-Charlie. It'll be research for the book.

39:20.875 --> 39:22.833
Okay? Be awesome.

39:26.791 --> 39:29.625
All right, so the idea is if we
can black out all the windows,

39:30.250 --> 39:32.250
it's efficient and it's safe.

39:32.333 --> 39:33.875
Is anybody else hearing this?

39:34.500 --> 39:36.083
How is driving blind safer?

39:36.166 --> 39:37.083
We're not.

39:37.166 --> 39:38.458
We've got the GPS.

40:00.541 --> 40:02.041
[engine starts]

40:04.041 --> 40:06.291
-[GPS beeps]
-[female voice] Calculating route.

40:06.833 --> 40:08.916
[seat belts click]

40:09.833 --> 40:10.666
[beep]

40:29.333 --> 40:31.500
-[GPS beeps]
-[female voice] Continue straight.

40:35.791 --> 40:38.625
In half a mile,
turn right onto Bay Street.

40:39.500 --> 40:41.500
-What is that?
-It's a curb.

40:41.583 --> 40:42.791
It's just a curb.

40:43.541 --> 40:45.583
[panting]

40:45.666 --> 40:47.458
[beeping]

40:48.125 --> 40:50.041
It's a proximity sensor.

41:02.833 --> 41:05.000
Just a speed bump. It's just a speed bump.

41:08.333 --> 41:09.875
[female voice] Turn right here.

41:12.208 --> 41:13.833
[beeping]

41:13.916 --> 41:14.833
[beeping faster]

41:21.625 --> 41:23.125
[beeping]

41:26.458 --> 41:28.708
[beeping faster]

41:28.791 --> 41:30.750
-Are we off the road?
-No, there's something.

41:31.333 --> 41:34.208
-I think it must be just a truck.
-Just go around.

41:34.291 --> 41:36.250
-Keep going around it.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

41:37.291 --> 41:38.666
[rumbling]

41:38.750 --> 41:39.958
What was that?

41:40.041 --> 41:41.041
[panting]

41:44.416 --> 41:46.375
[beeping]

41:46.958 --> 41:48.125
[beeping faster]

41:48.208 --> 41:50.291
[one continuous beep]

41:50.375 --> 41:52.041
Is somebody else driving out there?

41:55.125 --> 41:57.166
[rumbling]

42:03.708 --> 42:06.208
-[Malorie] Charlie, breathe.
-Shit! Fuck this shit.

42:06.291 --> 42:08.208
-Get the fuck out!
-Charlie! Calm down.

42:08.291 --> 42:10.291
Guys, stop touching him.

42:10.375 --> 42:12.916
-Look at me. You have to be quiet.
-Shut him up.

42:14.416 --> 42:16.166
[rumbling]

42:17.958 --> 42:19.750
[beeping]

42:21.666 --> 42:23.583
[distorted whispering]

42:23.666 --> 42:25.458
[Charlie] Ah. Ah!

42:25.541 --> 42:26.916
Fuck! We're not gonna make it.

42:28.958 --> 42:31.041
-[Charlie screams]
-Calm down. Calm down.

42:32.416 --> 42:34.333
-[Lucy] Oh, shit!
-Everybody, hold on.

42:34.416 --> 42:36.458
Hold on to something. Gonna move!

42:36.541 --> 42:37.916
-[tires screech]
-Ah!

42:38.833 --> 42:39.958
Hold on!

42:40.041 --> 42:41.500
That's not a fucking speed bump!

42:41.583 --> 42:43.541
-Fuck, it's stuck.
-Hold on.

42:44.541 --> 42:47.333
-[female voice] Turn left here.
-Slow down! Slow down!

42:47.416 --> 42:48.708
[tires squeal]

42:51.333 --> 42:52.500
[tires screech]

42:54.208 --> 42:55.708
[female voice] You have arrived.

42:57.833 --> 42:59.250
[Charlie] What the fuck?

42:59.333 --> 43:01.791
And after all this,
we're supposed to get out now?

43:02.583 --> 43:03.541
Lucky us.

43:08.000 --> 43:09.916
-[Tom] On three. One...
-[Charlie] I'm ready now.

43:10.000 --> 43:11.333
...two, three.

43:13.208 --> 43:15.375
[Malorie] What was that?
What did I just hit?

43:15.458 --> 43:16.875
[Charlie] That's just a pillar.

43:19.583 --> 43:20.916
[Douglas] Okay. Where's the--

43:21.000 --> 43:23.833
[Charlie] The door should be
just a couple of paces up, man.

43:23.916 --> 43:25.666
-[Tom] I'm lost.
-[Charlie] Towards your left.

43:25.750 --> 43:28.291
[Tom] Left. Left. I'm lost.

43:28.375 --> 43:30.541
-[Douglas] Come on, you guys.
-I'm lost.

43:30.625 --> 43:33.000
-Oh, here. Here.
-[Lucy] Okay. Okay.

43:33.083 --> 43:34.250
-You're in?
-No.

43:34.333 --> 43:35.708
Okay. Wait. Almost got it.

43:36.250 --> 43:37.166
Okay, I got it.

43:39.208 --> 43:40.125
Go on.

43:47.375 --> 43:48.541
All right. We're in.

43:50.666 --> 43:52.625
-Hello!
-Shh! Shh!

43:54.333 --> 43:55.500
I'll check the windows.

43:56.250 --> 43:57.958
Here we go. Here we go.

44:08.041 --> 44:10.833
[Tom] All right, I think we're clear.
You can take 'em off.

44:15.375 --> 44:16.875
Oh, my God.

44:17.458 --> 44:19.666
-Jack-fucking-pot.
-Yeah.

44:21.041 --> 44:22.750
-Where are the canned goods?
-Aisle two.

44:22.833 --> 44:24.166
-Toilet paper?
-Five.

44:24.250 --> 44:26.666
-Fuck that. Where's the booze?
-It's in seven.

44:26.750 --> 44:30.750
Let's not forget. We have limited space.
Stick to non-perishables, the necessities.

44:30.833 --> 44:32.625
-Where are the electronics?
-Go to six.

44:32.708 --> 44:34.458
[Tom] Six. All right. Cool. Thank you.

44:35.041 --> 44:36.541
I'm not cleaning this shit up.

44:39.375 --> 44:40.500
Sweet.

44:47.375 --> 44:49.291
Boy, I'm glad I tagged along.

44:49.875 --> 44:53.166
This is truly the happiest place on Earth.

44:53.250 --> 44:55.333
I know. You're not kidding!

45:00.791 --> 45:04.958
It's, uh... my baby shower gift to you.

45:06.708 --> 45:07.708
Why, thank you.

45:07.791 --> 45:09.000
[Tom] Yeah.

45:09.083 --> 45:12.208
So, my sister is
expecting her fourth, so...

45:12.708 --> 45:15.250
Oh, my God. She's a saint.

45:15.333 --> 45:16.541
Yeah, she is.

45:17.583 --> 45:19.708
And I'm always touching her belly.

45:20.958 --> 45:22.000
It's calming.

45:22.500 --> 45:24.750
Yeah, it's nature's dirty little trick.

45:28.958 --> 45:30.458
Is your sister in Sacramento?

45:32.500 --> 45:33.625
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

45:33.708 --> 45:34.666
Yeah.

45:38.583 --> 45:39.833
[grunts]

45:39.916 --> 45:42.750
What about you? Where did you--
Where did you grow up?

45:42.833 --> 45:44.333
Oh, just outside of Stockton.

45:44.416 --> 45:45.916
-Stockton.
-Yeah.

45:46.000 --> 45:48.041
-We raised horses.
-On a real ranch?

45:48.625 --> 45:52.500
-Well, my daddy was a real cowboy.
-That's--That's how you learned your...

45:52.583 --> 45:54.041
-What?
-...little shotgun trick.

45:54.125 --> 45:56.375
Yeah. I had an interesting childhood.

45:56.458 --> 45:57.333
Hmm.

45:58.041 --> 46:01.416
Ah, but Stockton wasn't
all that far from Sacramento.

46:01.500 --> 46:03.750
No. Just down 99.

46:03.833 --> 46:06.208
-Just down Highway 99.
-Worlds apart, right?

46:07.666 --> 46:10.125
Still we could've met some other way.

46:11.375 --> 46:12.333
Sure.

46:13.000 --> 46:15.125
Could have been your babysitter.

46:17.416 --> 46:19.041
My hot babysitter.

46:22.208 --> 46:26.041
You're... You're only saying that
'cause we're all gonna die.

46:27.791 --> 46:28.666
Possibly.

46:37.125 --> 46:38.625
[birds chirping]

47:05.750 --> 47:08.083
[whispers] How did you guys get so lucky?

47:09.458 --> 47:10.500
Huh?

47:12.041 --> 47:13.041
Hi.

47:15.208 --> 47:16.375
Hi, there.

47:20.750 --> 47:22.458
So sleepy.

47:23.125 --> 47:27.500
[Douglas] Attention, all shoppers,
come to aisle seven, please.

47:27.583 --> 47:31.541
I have a big, big, big, big, big
announcement to make.

47:31.625 --> 47:34.541
-Ladies and gentlemen, please...
-Yes, Douglas.

47:35.125 --> 47:40.833
I would like to take this opportunity
to make a toast to all of us...

47:41.416 --> 47:48.250
because all of us, collectively,
are making the end of the world...

47:51.666 --> 47:55.041
great again! Yeah!

47:58.083 --> 47:59.625
[birds chirping]

47:59.708 --> 48:00.583
Birdies.

48:02.500 --> 48:05.875
I mean, don't you doofuses get it?

48:06.583 --> 48:08.958
Uh, we could just stay here.

48:09.041 --> 48:14.250
We have a year's supply
of food and drink right here.

48:14.333 --> 48:17.666
We don't ever have to pay
and we shouldn't ever leave.

48:17.750 --> 48:19.958
And what are they gonna
do at Greg's? Starve?

48:22.000 --> 48:24.333
Better them than us. [laughs]

48:24.416 --> 48:27.708
We have everything we need to live here.
Everything.

48:27.791 --> 48:34.083
There is no statistical, logical, or legal
argument for trying to get back there.

48:34.166 --> 48:37.291
Here's an argument: we're not assholes.

48:39.541 --> 48:40.833
And we're not staying.

48:40.916 --> 48:42.458
[knock at door]

48:46.291 --> 48:47.833
[knock at door]

48:50.083 --> 48:51.000
What is it?

48:51.083 --> 48:52.958
[knocking]

48:55.958 --> 48:59.166
-[man] Somebody let me out of here.
-Charlie, what's behind there?

48:59.250 --> 49:00.416
It's a loading dock.

49:01.041 --> 49:02.000
[Tom] Hello?

49:02.958 --> 49:05.250
[man sobbing] Please let me in.

49:06.416 --> 49:07.916
[Tom] Speak up, I can't hear you.

49:08.000 --> 49:10.875
Please let me in.

49:11.625 --> 49:12.625
Cover your eyes.

49:12.708 --> 49:14.333
-[Malorie] What?
-I'm gonna open the door.

49:14.416 --> 49:16.541
-[Malorie] No.
-There's a person out there.

49:16.625 --> 49:18.250
I have to open the door.

49:20.666 --> 49:23.083
[Tom] Okay.

49:23.166 --> 49:24.291
Okay. Uh...

49:24.958 --> 49:25.958
Okay.

49:29.333 --> 49:30.875
-Hello?
-Hello.

49:31.500 --> 49:33.791
[man] Please let me in. I'm trapped.

49:33.875 --> 49:36.625
Wait, wait, wait. Is that...
Fish Fingers, is that you?

49:36.708 --> 49:39.958
-Charlie, yeah, it's me.
-[Malorie] Who's Fish Fingers, Charlie?

49:40.041 --> 49:43.000
He works here at the supermarket with me.
He works in the seafood department.

49:43.083 --> 49:46.458
He's been to prison and he's a bit crazy,
but he's always nice to me.

49:46.541 --> 49:48.833
-How did you get there, man?
-I got... I got...

49:48.916 --> 49:50.583
[stutters] They tricked me!

49:50.666 --> 49:51.625
Who's they?

49:51.708 --> 49:53.708
Who you talking about?
Are you there alone?

49:53.791 --> 49:55.750
They tricked me
and they left me to rot here.

49:55.833 --> 49:57.875
Who left you to rot?
What are you talking about?

49:57.958 --> 50:00.000
[Malorie] You guys,
there's something wrong.

50:00.083 --> 50:01.375
There's something wrong!

50:01.458 --> 50:04.375
-Please let me in. I'm trapped.
-Hey. Hey. Hey.

50:04.458 --> 50:06.750
What are you doin', Fish Fingers?
What are you doing, man?

50:07.750 --> 50:10.916
[Fish Fingers] Look at it!
It wants you to see it! Let me in!

50:12.291 --> 50:14.041
[shouting]

50:14.125 --> 50:17.083
[Lucy] He's too strong. I can't hold him.

50:17.166 --> 50:18.500
[Fish Fingers] Let me in!

50:18.583 --> 50:19.916
[Tom] Shit!

50:20.000 --> 50:21.875
[Fish Fingers grunting]

50:21.958 --> 50:23.625
[Malorie] Charlie! Charlie! Charlie!

50:23.708 --> 50:25.000
Fuck! Ah!

50:25.083 --> 50:26.416
[Malorie] Charlie, wait!

50:29.625 --> 50:32.083
[Fish Fingers]
Look at it, Charlie. It's beautiful.

50:32.166 --> 50:34.000
-Charlie?
-Charlie!

50:34.916 --> 50:35.916
[slashing sound]

50:36.000 --> 50:37.791
-Charlie!
-[Douglas] Charlie!

50:37.875 --> 50:39.791
-Oh, shit.
-[Lucy] Oh, fuck.

50:39.875 --> 50:41.875
[Lucy screaming]

50:43.041 --> 50:44.041
Fuck!

50:45.750 --> 50:47.083
[panting]

50:47.166 --> 50:48.291
[Tom] We gotta go.

50:49.833 --> 50:51.666
We gotta move. Come on. Let's go.

50:51.750 --> 50:52.958
Let's get out of here.

50:54.583 --> 50:56.333
[pounding on door]

50:56.958 --> 50:59.958
[Fish Fingers] Please. Please let me in.

51:00.041 --> 51:02.041
[Douglas] How is that guy alive in there?

51:02.625 --> 51:04.333
[Fish fingers] Please let me in.

51:04.833 --> 51:06.666
[pounding on door]

51:27.958 --> 51:29.583
Hi, Felix!

51:30.750 --> 51:33.166
Oh, my God. Look at all this stuff.

51:33.958 --> 51:36.083
-Birdies?
-[Malorie] Yeah, they, uh...

51:36.166 --> 51:38.666
They seem to sense
when the creatures are around.

51:39.250 --> 51:40.625
Where's Charlie?

51:42.583 --> 51:45.291
Another novel I won't have to read.

51:45.375 --> 51:47.791
He saved us, you fucking asshole.

52:09.458 --> 52:12.208
[Douglas] I know what you think of me,
what everybody thinks of me.

52:12.291 --> 52:14.208
You know, in the divorce petition...

52:15.166 --> 52:20.625
my first wife said that to call me a creep
would be an affront to creeps everywhere.

52:20.708 --> 52:22.208
[liquor pouring]

52:22.291 --> 52:25.291
My second wife said
she no longer feared going to hell,

52:25.375 --> 52:28.416
'cause it couldn't possibly be worse
than being married to me.

52:29.000 --> 52:30.583
Think I would have loved them.

52:30.666 --> 52:31.541
[Douglas] Maybe.

52:32.125 --> 52:33.208
And then Lydia.

52:34.166 --> 52:37.083
Third time really was the charm for me.

52:38.625 --> 52:40.875
She was the kindest person I ever met.

52:41.791 --> 52:44.375
But I'm here and she's gone.
You know why that is?

52:44.458 --> 52:47.041
Because, in the end,
there are only two types of people.

52:47.125 --> 52:49.125
The assholes and the dead.

52:49.208 --> 52:51.416
[Malorie] God, you sound like my father.

52:52.083 --> 52:53.250
Like your father? Why?

52:53.333 --> 52:58.583
Was he a towering intellect given
to dispensing wisdom to undeserving fools?

52:58.666 --> 53:00.500
Yes, he was fluent in asshole as well.

53:01.541 --> 53:06.458
And just like you, he blamed
everything he did on some deeper meaning,

53:07.041 --> 53:09.125
convoluted conspiracy theories and...

53:10.375 --> 53:13.041
how it was everybody else's fault
when he was clearly in the wrong.

53:13.125 --> 53:16.458
But, you know, once my sister and I
realized it was just an excuse

53:16.541 --> 53:20.250
to treat his family like shit,
it made life a little easier.

53:20.333 --> 53:23.291
You know what though?
I see one difference between us.

53:24.500 --> 53:25.458
Hmm?

53:25.541 --> 53:26.583
I'm never wrong.

53:27.166 --> 53:28.291
You are...

53:28.375 --> 53:29.791
You're two pricks in a pod.

53:30.791 --> 53:32.333
Do I look like him as well?

53:33.166 --> 53:34.125
Mm...

53:35.166 --> 53:36.166
Not really.

53:37.166 --> 53:40.458
-He wasn't exquisitely handsome?
-It's not that, it's just...

53:42.375 --> 53:44.458
the hair... the hair is different.

53:44.541 --> 53:45.916
-The hair?
-Yeah.

53:46.958 --> 53:48.041
He had some.

53:48.625 --> 53:49.458
Oh.

53:58.375 --> 54:00.041
Oh, I can't.

54:00.125 --> 54:02.875
Oh, come on, the world is ending.

54:02.958 --> 54:06.875
I really don't think a quarter-ounce
of whiskey's gonna tip the scales, do you?

54:08.708 --> 54:09.541
[grunts]

54:10.375 --> 54:11.291
Well...

54:12.416 --> 54:13.833
I hope you're wrong.

54:14.916 --> 54:16.708
About the assholes and the dead.

54:19.000 --> 54:20.375
I hope there is more.

54:22.125 --> 54:24.375
Here's to hoping there is more.

54:39.083 --> 54:40.500
[car engine starts]

54:47.458 --> 54:49.208
-[Tom] Close the garage.
-I've got it.

54:50.666 --> 54:52.083
-[Tom] Wait. Wait. Wait.
-[beep]

54:52.166 --> 54:53.791
-Cover your eyes.
-[Douglas] Yeah.

54:53.875 --> 54:56.541
[Malorie] Okay, okay, okay.
It's closed. It's closed.

54:58.166 --> 54:59.458
[Douglas] Sons of bitches.

55:00.458 --> 55:02.250
Where's the goddamn car?

55:02.333 --> 55:04.458
You guys.
You guys, where are Lucy and Felix?

55:09.208 --> 55:10.250
[Malorie moans]

55:13.333 --> 55:14.375
Fuck.

55:17.791 --> 55:19.125
[sighs]

55:34.125 --> 55:35.791
[panting]

55:43.416 --> 55:44.583
You stopped rowing.

55:45.458 --> 55:46.791
I'm just taking a break.

55:48.083 --> 55:49.583
How much longer?

55:49.666 --> 55:50.708
A few hours.

56:10.833 --> 56:11.958
[Boy] Ah!

56:15.500 --> 56:16.875
[Boy] Malorie!

56:17.916 --> 56:20.333
Malorie! Malorie!

56:20.416 --> 56:21.541
Help!

56:23.041 --> 56:23.875
Malorie!

56:27.208 --> 56:28.500
[grunts]

56:28.583 --> 56:29.541
[panting]

56:29.625 --> 56:31.791
-Are you okay? Are you okay?
-Yes.

56:31.875 --> 56:34.333
-I'm cold.
-I know. I know you're cold. Hold on.

56:37.750 --> 56:42.291
No, no, no, no, no, no.
All the food and blankets. God damn it!

56:42.375 --> 56:43.208
[grunts]

56:43.291 --> 56:45.125
-I'm sorry.
-[Malorie] No, no, it's...

56:45.208 --> 56:46.166
Hold on.

56:46.791 --> 56:48.791
Okay. All right.

56:48.875 --> 56:51.333
-Okay.
-[coughs] I'm so cold.

56:51.916 --> 56:55.083
We're gonna get you warmed up, okay?
We're gonna get you warmed up.

56:56.833 --> 56:59.000
Put this around you.

56:59.083 --> 57:01.041
Keep your blindfolds on. Stay tight.

57:02.625 --> 57:04.083
[wind chimes clanking]

57:05.083 --> 57:06.583
Did you hear that?

57:06.666 --> 57:07.666
Did you hear that?

57:08.458 --> 57:10.291
[grunting]

57:18.500 --> 57:21.041
Lay down on the bottom of the boat.
Lay down, really flat.

57:21.125 --> 57:23.541
I need you to be quiet.
I'm gonna leave the birds with you.

57:23.625 --> 57:26.541
I'm gonna cover you up, but do not
make a sound and do not leave this boat.

57:26.625 --> 57:28.083
Understand? Do not leave this boat!

57:29.416 --> 57:31.416
[panting]

59:00.500 --> 59:01.625
Shit.

59:38.041 --> 59:39.166
[metal clang]

59:42.500 --> 59:44.541
[metal clanging]

1:00:11.041 --> 1:00:12.875
[wind whistles]

1:00:12.958 --> 1:00:15.416
[rumbling]

1:00:43.750 --> 1:00:45.125
[rumbling]

1:00:49.708 --> 1:00:51.416
[distorted whispering] Malorie.

1:00:51.500 --> 1:00:53.250
Malorie.

1:00:53.333 --> 1:00:54.333
[grunts]

1:00:55.750 --> 1:00:57.666
Malorie.

1:01:05.625 --> 1:01:06.958
[gunshots]

1:01:07.041 --> 1:01:09.833
Something is wrong with Malorie.

1:01:09.916 --> 1:01:12.166
[distorted whispering] Malorie.

1:01:12.250 --> 1:01:13.333
Ah! Ah!

1:01:13.416 --> 1:01:15.583
[rumbling]

1:01:25.416 --> 1:01:27.541
[panting]

1:01:29.333 --> 1:01:31.541
[distorted whispering]

1:01:46.791 --> 1:01:47.833
Malorie?

1:01:53.541 --> 1:01:54.583
Malorie?

1:01:58.541 --> 1:02:00.291
-[distorted whispers]
-Malorie?

1:02:06.875 --> 1:02:07.875
[Malorie grunts]

1:02:07.958 --> 1:02:09.916
I told you to stay on the boat.

1:02:10.000 --> 1:02:11.041
You don't think.

1:02:11.125 --> 1:02:13.500
You do exactly what I say or you die,
do you understand me?

1:02:13.583 --> 1:02:16.250
If something happens to me,
do not try and help me.

1:02:16.333 --> 1:02:18.166
Forget about me and try to save yourself.

1:02:18.250 --> 1:02:19.625
Do you understand?

1:02:19.708 --> 1:02:22.833
Say it! If something happens to me,
what do you do?

1:02:22.916 --> 1:02:25.291
You save yourself. Say it!

1:02:25.916 --> 1:02:27.916
-I save myself.
-You save yourself.

1:02:29.375 --> 1:02:31.083
[Malorie] I can't trust you.

1:02:49.583 --> 1:02:52.833
[Malorie]
The end of the world makes us do things.

1:02:54.166 --> 1:02:56.833
-[Tom] It's not the end of the world.
-[Malorie] Really?

1:02:57.541 --> 1:02:58.791
It sure feels like it.

1:03:02.541 --> 1:03:08.250
At the end of my deployment in Iraq,
we were stationed at this village...

1:03:10.541 --> 1:03:13.500
ordered to patrol the streets,
make sure everybody was safe.

1:03:15.833 --> 1:03:16.958
One morning, we saw...

1:03:18.416 --> 1:03:21.000
this father walking with his four kids.

1:03:21.083 --> 1:03:23.458
So I pulled over to make sure
everything was okay

1:03:23.541 --> 1:03:26.166
and to make sure he got
wherever he was going safely.

1:03:29.166 --> 1:03:31.333
Come to find out,
he was walking his kids to school.

1:03:33.583 --> 1:03:36.166
In the middle of all that shit,

1:03:36.750 --> 1:03:39.250
all that chaos,
he was walking his kids to school.

1:03:46.333 --> 1:03:47.208
So...

1:03:50.791 --> 1:03:52.208
So we just followed him.

1:03:53.750 --> 1:03:54.833
Day after day.

1:03:55.458 --> 1:03:56.500
We escorted him.

1:03:59.958 --> 1:04:01.416
That just became our routine.

1:04:05.000 --> 1:04:06.500
And then, at the end of our time,

1:04:06.583 --> 1:04:10.250
he gave me this
when it was time to come back home.

1:04:16.750 --> 1:04:17.625
Mm.

1:04:23.833 --> 1:04:26.500
I like to think he's still
walking his kids to school.

1:05:06.166 --> 1:05:07.208
[beep]

1:05:07.291 --> 1:05:09.458
[Malorie]
Hello, can anybody hear me? Hello?

1:05:09.541 --> 1:05:12.125
This is Malorie.
Anybody, can you hear me? Hello?

1:05:12.208 --> 1:05:13.541
[static]

1:05:15.250 --> 1:05:18.583
Can anybody hear me? Hello?
Hello? Can anybody hear me?

1:05:20.958 --> 1:05:22.833
Hello? Testing, hello?

1:05:24.041 --> 1:05:25.125
[static]

1:05:25.208 --> 1:05:27.166
Hello, is anyone out there? Hello?

1:05:28.041 --> 1:05:30.125
[Olympia] Can you hear me, please?

1:05:30.208 --> 1:05:32.208
-Hello? Testing.
-[Olympia] Are you a...

1:05:32.291 --> 1:05:33.708
Do you have a blindfold on?

1:05:34.375 --> 1:05:37.625
You do.
Is-- Is the blanket behind you still up?

1:05:37.708 --> 1:05:39.791
[sighs] Ah...

1:05:39.875 --> 1:05:42.250
Okay, just come in really, really quickly.

1:05:42.333 --> 1:05:45.791
Thank you. Here's my blindfold.
Thank you so much.

1:05:45.875 --> 1:05:49.375
It's okay. Just wait. Wait here. Malorie!

1:05:49.458 --> 1:05:51.208
-I gotta pee.
-Olympia, what are you doing?

1:05:51.291 --> 1:05:52.541
-Malorie!
-What are you doing?

1:05:52.625 --> 1:05:56.416
-What are you thinking? Get down!
-[Olympia] Okay, he's just scared.

1:05:56.500 --> 1:05:58.458
-He's just scared.
-Tom. Check the bag.

1:05:58.541 --> 1:06:01.041
-Get over here, Olympia. Get over here.
-[grunts]

1:06:01.125 --> 1:06:02.750
-Who are you?
-Who is this guy?

1:06:02.833 --> 1:06:05.083
Tom, I've got him. Check the bag.
Check the bag.

1:06:05.666 --> 1:06:07.041
-Who is this?
-He's just scared.

1:06:07.125 --> 1:06:08.583
-Who are you?
-How did he get in here?

1:06:08.666 --> 1:06:12.208
-Shut up, Olympia. Who are you?
-He was scared, okay? I just let him in.

1:06:12.291 --> 1:06:14.666
-You let a stranger in the house!
-I'm sorry.

1:06:14.750 --> 1:06:16.416
-He was terrified!
-Are you a simpleton?

1:06:16.958 --> 1:06:18.958
Oh, God. Okay. Please.

1:06:19.041 --> 1:06:20.416
My name is Gary.

1:06:21.291 --> 1:06:22.416
I live in the city.

1:06:22.916 --> 1:06:25.666
When these things came, I got
the first train out with some colleagues

1:06:25.750 --> 1:06:27.250
because we thought it would be safe.

1:06:29.833 --> 1:06:34.041
Please, please just let me stay here.
They're after me.

1:06:34.625 --> 1:06:35.875
Who's after you?

1:06:36.500 --> 1:06:38.583
-I don't believe it. He's lying.
-Who's after you?

1:06:38.666 --> 1:06:39.791
It's obvious he's lying.

1:06:39.875 --> 1:06:41.375
-I swear.
-Why are you here?

1:06:41.458 --> 1:06:45.416
We went
to my colleague Carl's house to lay low.

1:06:45.500 --> 1:06:49.250
Everything was fine until they broke in.

1:06:50.541 --> 1:06:52.333
Creatures don't break into people's homes.

1:06:52.416 --> 1:06:54.500
No, not the creatures, these psychos.

1:06:56.375 --> 1:06:58.333
These psychos from Northwood.

1:06:58.416 --> 1:07:00.833
[Malorie] Northwood?
I don't... Where is that?

1:07:00.916 --> 1:07:03.625
It's a mental institution
for the criminally insane.

1:07:03.708 --> 1:07:06.916
Well, it's nice to know
they have hall passes now.

1:07:07.708 --> 1:07:08.583
And then what?

1:07:08.666 --> 1:07:13.000
They took us outside
and they forced our eyes open

1:07:13.083 --> 1:07:15.458
so that we would have
to look at the creatures.

1:07:17.041 --> 1:07:18.041
[Malorie] What?

1:07:18.875 --> 1:07:21.041
-Did you look?
-No.

1:07:21.125 --> 1:07:26.916
Somehow, my friend Carl managed to tackle
one of these people to the ground

1:07:27.000 --> 1:07:29.125
and the rest of us made a run for it.

1:07:29.208 --> 1:07:32.625
I just kept on running
and running and running till I got here.

1:07:33.791 --> 1:07:37.375
I've been knocking on
all the doors and nobody answered.

1:07:38.958 --> 1:07:40.750
Until you did, so...

1:07:41.250 --> 1:07:42.250
[sobs]

1:07:42.791 --> 1:07:43.666
Thank you.

1:07:44.791 --> 1:07:45.833
[sighs]

1:07:50.583 --> 1:07:51.500
[birds chirping]

1:07:54.458 --> 1:07:55.416
Birds.

1:07:56.666 --> 1:08:01.625
The scariest thing was, uh...
when these people broke in, they...

1:08:04.000 --> 1:08:05.833
they weren't wearing blindfolds.

1:08:07.625 --> 1:08:09.083
It's like they didn't need them.

1:08:09.166 --> 1:08:11.666
But they'd been outside.
You have to wear blindfolds.

1:08:11.750 --> 1:08:12.750
Not these people.

1:08:13.916 --> 1:08:16.833
These crazy guys
weren't affected like everyone else.

1:08:16.916 --> 1:08:18.458
They wanted to see.

1:08:19.166 --> 1:08:20.041
They were happy.

1:08:21.250 --> 1:08:23.458
They were so glad.

1:08:25.208 --> 1:08:28.500
And they said everyone needed to see.

1:08:32.500 --> 1:08:34.458
[gasps] Wait.

1:08:34.541 --> 1:08:37.333
[Douglas] Get up and get out.
It's not an orphanage.

1:08:37.416 --> 1:08:41.916
New guy, you had a great visit.
We really loved meeting you. Now fuck off.

1:08:42.500 --> 1:08:46.333
And anybody who doesn't agree,
you go with him.

1:08:46.416 --> 1:08:48.583
-Out now!
-Douglas, that is murder.

1:08:48.666 --> 1:08:50.083
No. This is murder.

1:08:50.166 --> 1:08:53.041
-Please.
-Letting strangers into this house.

1:08:53.625 --> 1:08:58.583
Every contact we have had
with the outside has brought us death.

1:08:58.666 --> 1:09:00.583
Lydia, Greg, Charlie.

1:09:00.666 --> 1:09:02.583
If you wanna save people out there,

1:09:02.666 --> 1:09:05.541
then you go right through that door
and you go do it.

1:09:05.625 --> 1:09:08.375
We're not bringing
any more strangers in here.

1:09:08.958 --> 1:09:10.250
Not while I'm alive.

1:09:10.333 --> 1:09:13.166
I won't tell you again, get up and get--

1:09:21.750 --> 1:09:22.750
Thank you.

1:09:23.875 --> 1:09:25.583
[Tom] You'll sleep in the garage.

1:09:26.500 --> 1:09:27.375
[Tom grunts]

1:09:35.333 --> 1:09:37.125
The only reason I opened that door

1:09:37.208 --> 1:09:39.875
is 'cause I remember
what it felt like to be outside of it.

1:09:41.083 --> 1:09:43.166
If you guys hadn't let me in, I...

1:09:44.083 --> 1:09:46.166
[chuckles] I feel like such a burden.

1:09:46.250 --> 1:09:48.791
You are no more a burden than I am, okay?

1:09:48.875 --> 1:09:50.458
-That's not true.
-It is. It is.

1:09:50.541 --> 1:09:52.041
You're not soft like me.

1:09:53.041 --> 1:09:55.583
I'm so spoiled.

1:09:56.458 --> 1:10:00.708
My parents have always done
everything for me and then my husband,

1:10:00.791 --> 1:10:04.166
and I just...
I got soft from all that love.

1:10:05.500 --> 1:10:08.458
Well, I was raised by wolves,
so consider yourself lucky.

1:10:12.208 --> 1:10:17.250
If something happens to me,
I want you to take care of my baby.

1:10:18.125 --> 1:10:19.041
Okay?

1:10:19.541 --> 1:10:20.791
-No. No.
-Please.

1:10:20.875 --> 1:10:22.166
-It's your baby.
-Malorie.

1:10:22.250 --> 1:10:23.500
No.

1:10:23.583 --> 1:10:25.750
-Promise me.
-Nothing is gonna happen to you.

1:10:25.833 --> 1:10:26.666
It's your baby.

1:10:26.750 --> 1:10:27.750
-Promise me.
-Nothing--

1:10:27.833 --> 1:10:29.458
Please promise me.

1:10:31.958 --> 1:10:34.125
Yeah, okay. Yeah, of course.

1:10:41.750 --> 1:10:43.041
What is this?

1:10:44.083 --> 1:10:45.791
Well, if I was just gonna tell you,

1:10:45.875 --> 1:10:49.750
I wouldn't have bothered
putting it in this fancy-- this fancy bag.

1:10:54.041 --> 1:10:54.916
[Olympia laughs]

1:10:55.000 --> 1:10:56.666
I got it on the supply run.

1:11:00.875 --> 1:11:03.125
-It's so cute. [chuckles]
-Mm-hmm.

1:11:04.416 --> 1:11:05.791
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

1:11:10.833 --> 1:11:13.333
I know it's not the baby shower
you've always dreamt of.

1:11:13.416 --> 1:11:15.958
No, it's-- It's perfect.

1:11:16.958 --> 1:11:20.500
And you can give it to your little one
when she's old enough, okay?

1:11:23.791 --> 1:11:24.791
[Olympia] Thank you.

1:11:41.000 --> 1:11:41.958
[panting]

1:11:42.041 --> 1:11:45.000
You guys, the river's speeding up.
It's time for a meeting.

1:11:54.541 --> 1:11:55.583
[clears throat]

1:11:59.708 --> 1:12:01.875
I need to talk to you about the rapids.

1:12:02.541 --> 1:12:04.875
The rapids are
where the water gets very bumpy.

1:12:04.958 --> 1:12:08.166
It's very loud. It's very dangerous,

1:12:08.250 --> 1:12:10.916
and it's gonna be
the hardest thing we have ever done.

1:12:12.375 --> 1:12:17.333
And when we reach them, one of you
is gonna have a very important job.

1:12:20.000 --> 1:12:22.041
One of you is gonna have to look.

1:12:24.375 --> 1:12:27.375
And the person who looks,

1:12:28.458 --> 1:12:31.333
they have to tell me
which direction to steer into

1:12:31.416 --> 1:12:33.041
so that I go the right way.

1:12:34.666 --> 1:12:37.375
Because if I look, we won't make it.

1:12:41.125 --> 1:12:42.791
What if we see something?

1:12:43.791 --> 1:12:45.500
-I'll do it.
-No, no, no, no.

1:12:45.583 --> 1:12:48.833
I'm-- I'm the one
who will say who looks, okay? I say it.

1:12:49.416 --> 1:12:51.875
I'll say who goes. I'll say who looks.

1:12:52.458 --> 1:12:53.625
I say who looks.

1:13:03.625 --> 1:13:05.500
♪ To live without you ♪

1:13:05.583 --> 1:13:08.666
♪ Would only be heartbreak for me ♪

1:13:11.333 --> 1:13:13.291
["I Say a Little Prayer" playing]

1:13:18.125 --> 1:13:20.041
♪ I say a little prayer for you ♪

1:13:20.125 --> 1:13:21.125
[beeps]

1:13:21.625 --> 1:13:24.916
Testing. Testing. Hello?
Hello? Is anyone out there?

1:13:25.000 --> 1:13:27.125
Hello? Testing, one, two, three. Hello?

1:13:27.208 --> 1:13:28.125
[static]

1:13:28.208 --> 1:13:29.166
[grunts]

1:13:29.958 --> 1:13:30.958
[Malorie] Testing.

1:13:31.041 --> 1:13:32.000
[walkie-talkie beeps]

1:13:32.083 --> 1:13:34.125
♪ Forever and ever
You'll stay in my heart ♪

1:13:34.208 --> 1:13:36.375
-I love this song.
-Me too.

1:13:36.458 --> 1:13:37.708
-Me too.
-Me too.

1:13:38.916 --> 1:13:40.875
-I've never actually heard it before.
-Hmm.

1:13:40.958 --> 1:13:43.333
♪ Together forever
That's how must be ♪

1:13:43.416 --> 1:13:46.958
♪ To live without you
Would only be heartbreak for me... ♪

1:13:47.041 --> 1:13:48.250
[grunts]

1:13:48.875 --> 1:13:49.916
[grunts]

1:13:50.500 --> 1:13:53.458
[Olympia groaning]

1:13:54.583 --> 1:13:57.291
-It could be a false alarm, right?
-[Cheryl] All right.

1:13:57.375 --> 1:13:58.875
We're going upstairs to the bedroom.

1:13:58.958 --> 1:14:03.166
We need towels, sponges,
um... scissors, and lots of water.

1:14:03.250 --> 1:14:06.666
Buckets of water. It's okay. It's okay.

1:14:07.291 --> 1:14:09.000
-It's okay.
-[Olympia panting]

1:14:09.083 --> 1:14:10.666
-[Cheryl] It's okay.
-[bird chirps]

1:14:10.750 --> 1:14:12.708
Take it easy. I've got you.

1:14:12.791 --> 1:14:15.083
-[Olympia groans]
-[Cheryl] It's okay. It's okay.

1:14:15.166 --> 1:14:16.250
[music stops]

1:14:22.125 --> 1:14:24.125
[liquid trickling]

1:14:45.208 --> 1:14:50.291
Ah, the scissors are in the, um, drawer
by the side of your left hand. Yeah.

1:14:57.916 --> 1:14:58.916
[Malorie exhales]

1:15:01.958 --> 1:15:05.291
-Okay, so the baby's coming.
-No, not happening.

1:15:05.375 --> 1:15:07.625
-Not happening. [groans]
-It's definitely coming.

1:15:07.708 --> 1:15:10.083
-Come with me. Come with me.
-This is not happening.

1:15:10.166 --> 1:15:12.750
-It's happening. Let's go. Come on. Hey.
-[moaning]

1:15:12.833 --> 1:15:15.125
-I have to do the water.
-We'll do the water.

1:15:15.208 --> 1:15:17.000
[grunts]

1:15:22.083 --> 1:15:23.791
Okay, here we go.

1:15:24.625 --> 1:15:26.125
[both panting]

1:15:29.541 --> 1:15:31.458
-You two are doing great.
-Oh, shut up.

1:15:31.541 --> 1:15:33.291
[Olympia grunting]

1:15:34.833 --> 1:15:36.458
[classical music playing]

1:15:36.541 --> 1:15:38.541
[women groaning]

1:15:58.416 --> 1:15:59.875
[screams]

1:15:59.958 --> 1:16:02.291
[panting]

1:16:02.375 --> 1:16:03.458
[Cheryl] One more time.

1:16:03.541 --> 1:16:05.250
Come on. Come on.

1:16:06.958 --> 1:16:08.500
[humming]

1:16:33.833 --> 1:16:35.666
[Malorie grunting]

1:16:35.750 --> 1:16:37.125
[screams]

1:16:42.375 --> 1:16:44.166
It's okay. It's okay.

1:16:46.125 --> 1:16:47.625
[baby cries]

1:16:47.708 --> 1:16:48.833
It's a boy.

1:16:48.916 --> 1:16:50.375
[baby crying]

1:16:50.458 --> 1:16:51.500
[Malorie] Oh.

1:16:54.166 --> 1:16:55.125
No.

1:16:56.583 --> 1:16:59.083
And your auntie thought you'd be a girl.

1:17:01.416 --> 1:17:02.666
[sighs]

1:17:02.750 --> 1:17:04.333
[baby crying]

1:17:22.833 --> 1:17:24.416
[pounding on door]

1:17:24.500 --> 1:17:27.375
Hey, new guy. New guy, let me in.

1:17:27.458 --> 1:17:30.625
Just come and unlock the door. Come on.

1:17:30.708 --> 1:17:32.541
Let me out. What are you doing?

1:17:34.333 --> 1:17:35.208
What?

1:17:41.791 --> 1:17:42.833
What are you doing?

1:17:50.625 --> 1:17:51.875
[sighs]

1:17:59.500 --> 1:18:00.500
Gary?

1:18:03.291 --> 1:18:04.416
Gary!

1:18:04.500 --> 1:18:06.500
Hey.

1:18:06.583 --> 1:18:09.416
[pounds on door]
Tom! He put the birds in the freezer.

1:18:09.500 --> 1:18:12.416
Tom, I told you he's fucking crazy.

1:18:22.583 --> 1:18:23.458
Ga--

1:18:27.166 --> 1:18:29.833
Tom. Get the shotgun.

1:18:29.916 --> 1:18:31.291
He's crazy.

1:18:38.125 --> 1:18:42.666
What the fuck are you doing?
We let you into this house. We let--

1:18:48.958 --> 1:18:51.125
No! No! Fuck.

1:18:51.833 --> 1:18:55.750
Fucking asshole.
I knew you were a fucking lunatic.

1:18:55.833 --> 1:18:58.708
You fucking piece of shit. We saved you.

1:18:59.833 --> 1:19:00.750
Fuck!

1:19:04.958 --> 1:19:06.500
[screams]

1:19:07.083 --> 1:19:10.208
-[Cheryl] Almost there.
-That's right. That's right.

1:19:10.291 --> 1:19:12.208
Yes! Yes!

1:19:12.916 --> 1:19:13.833
Yes.

1:19:13.916 --> 1:19:14.875
Oh.

1:19:14.958 --> 1:19:17.208
You did it, Mama. You did it.

1:19:17.291 --> 1:19:19.041
[baby cries]

1:19:21.208 --> 1:19:22.083
Oh.

1:19:22.708 --> 1:19:23.666
Hello.

1:19:25.250 --> 1:19:26.416
You look so beautiful.

1:19:26.500 --> 1:19:28.291
What's going on down there?

1:19:31.125 --> 1:19:32.000
Can I see?

1:19:42.166 --> 1:19:43.750
So beautiful.

1:19:43.833 --> 1:19:44.958
[Olympia] Thank you.

1:19:47.458 --> 1:19:48.708
Can I see yours?

1:19:56.625 --> 1:19:57.500
Wow.

1:20:00.083 --> 1:20:00.958
Hum.

1:20:01.750 --> 1:20:02.958
Thank you.

1:20:05.166 --> 1:20:06.333
Look at this.

1:20:07.291 --> 1:20:08.291
Look at this.

1:20:09.500 --> 1:20:10.541
[screams]

1:20:10.625 --> 1:20:12.708
-[Malorie] Olympia, cover your eyes.
-Isn't it beautiful?

1:20:12.791 --> 1:20:16.041
No. Why are you doing this?
Gary, please don't do this.

1:20:17.125 --> 1:20:18.833
-Look.
-Gary, please don't do this.

1:20:18.916 --> 1:20:21.375
-Show the baby.
-[Malorie] No, no, no, Olympia.

1:20:21.458 --> 1:20:23.125
Olympia, cover the baby's eyes.

1:20:23.208 --> 1:20:24.333
Olympia.

1:20:25.000 --> 1:20:26.250
See?

1:20:27.333 --> 1:20:29.958
-Show your baby.
-[Malorie] Olympia, let me see your baby.

1:20:30.708 --> 1:20:33.000
-You're not so bad.
-Olympia, let me see your baby.

1:20:34.375 --> 1:20:37.666
Keep the baby's eyes covered.
Let me see your baby, just for one minute.

1:20:37.750 --> 1:20:41.250
Olympia, let me hold your baby
just for one minute!

1:20:41.333 --> 1:20:42.291
Just one minute.

1:20:42.375 --> 1:20:44.583
Let me hold her for one minute, okay?

1:20:44.666 --> 1:20:46.250
-One minute.
-[Gary] See.

1:20:46.333 --> 1:20:48.416
-[Malorie] Okay?
-[Gary] See.

1:20:50.541 --> 1:20:51.541
See!

1:20:55.583 --> 1:20:56.458
[thud]

1:20:56.541 --> 1:21:00.875
[Cheryl] No. Oh, no. Oh, please, no. Oh!

1:21:00.958 --> 1:21:05.875
-See it. See it.
-No, no, no. No, no, no.

1:21:06.750 --> 1:21:08.125
[screams]

1:21:23.833 --> 1:21:25.666
[babies crying]

1:21:37.500 --> 1:21:38.833
Hey, Malorie.

1:21:40.208 --> 1:21:41.416
Give me the children.

1:21:43.958 --> 1:21:45.333
Give me the kids.

1:21:46.666 --> 1:21:48.666
Give me the children or I'll take them!

1:21:48.750 --> 1:21:50.625
Hey, asshole.

1:21:51.375 --> 1:21:52.291
Hey.

1:21:54.166 --> 1:21:55.166
What are you doing here?

1:21:59.291 --> 1:22:00.375
Have you come to see?

1:22:02.541 --> 1:22:03.666
Open your eyes.

1:22:07.666 --> 1:22:09.333
Don't be frightened.

1:22:10.916 --> 1:22:12.416
Look at me. Look at me.

1:22:12.500 --> 1:22:14.500
Look at me. Look at me!

1:22:16.250 --> 1:22:17.125
[Gary grunts]

1:22:21.166 --> 1:22:22.166
Ow.

1:22:27.041 --> 1:22:28.000
[grunts]

1:22:35.500 --> 1:22:36.875
[groans]

1:22:36.958 --> 1:22:38.208
[Douglas panting]

1:22:43.166 --> 1:22:44.166
[grunts]

1:22:48.541 --> 1:22:49.750
I'm sorry.

1:22:49.833 --> 1:22:51.083
[babies crying]

1:22:53.125 --> 1:22:55.666
I'm sorry that you didn't get to see.

1:22:57.000 --> 1:22:58.541
It is beautiful.

1:22:59.541 --> 1:23:01.000
So beautiful.

1:23:04.083 --> 1:23:05.250
I'm sorry.

1:23:07.875 --> 1:23:08.750
[grunts]

1:23:09.916 --> 1:23:11.708
It shall cleanse the world.

1:23:11.791 --> 1:23:13.000
[panting]

1:23:40.208 --> 1:23:42.208
[gunshots]

1:23:43.291 --> 1:23:44.791
[babies crying]

1:23:56.750 --> 1:23:59.916
Please don't. Please don't hurt us.
Please stay away from us.

1:24:00.000 --> 1:24:02.458
Please. Please. Please. Please.

1:24:02.541 --> 1:24:05.333
Please don't do this. Don't do this.
Please don't do this.

1:24:09.291 --> 1:24:11.750
It's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

1:24:37.958 --> 1:24:39.541
[Malorie] Listen to the clicks.

1:24:40.375 --> 1:24:43.625
Listen to the sounds,
if they're softer or louder.

1:24:44.750 --> 1:24:45.958
Listen to this.

1:24:46.708 --> 1:24:48.166
Listen.

1:24:49.083 --> 1:24:51.708
If they're louder,
you're in an open space. Do you hear that?

1:24:51.791 --> 1:24:55.000
But if they're softer,
something is very close.

1:24:55.083 --> 1:24:57.458
Please. Anyone. Hello? Hello?

1:24:58.250 --> 1:24:59.541
Hello, hel--

1:24:59.625 --> 1:25:00.583
[static]

1:25:00.666 --> 1:25:01.541
[beeps]

1:25:03.041 --> 1:25:03.916
Hello?

1:25:43.416 --> 1:25:44.708
[vehicle approaching]

1:25:53.833 --> 1:25:55.375
[man] Check it out. Yeah.

1:25:57.333 --> 1:25:59.291
[woman] There is nothing here.

1:25:59.875 --> 1:26:02.500
-[man] Let's go to another spot.
-[woman] Fucking time.

1:26:11.166 --> 1:26:12.666
[panting]

1:26:26.916 --> 1:26:28.916
-Hey.
-Hey.

1:26:52.708 --> 1:26:53.708
What's wrong?

1:26:55.583 --> 1:26:57.208
I heard some of them again.

1:26:58.500 --> 1:26:59.458
What?

1:27:00.750 --> 1:27:01.791
A few of 'em...

1:27:02.750 --> 1:27:03.625
driving around.

1:27:05.375 --> 1:27:07.833
Driving around like
they're not blindfolded.

1:27:09.875 --> 1:27:10.833
Okay.

1:27:12.583 --> 1:27:13.791
No more runs alone.

1:27:15.583 --> 1:27:16.541
Okay.

1:27:21.750 --> 1:27:23.666
-[bell rings]
-What's this?

1:27:24.250 --> 1:27:26.708
I was thinking like
a warning system for the kids.

1:27:26.791 --> 1:27:30.958
-If they're in trouble, ring the bell.
-Right. That's nice.

1:27:37.041 --> 1:27:38.041
How about this?

1:27:39.125 --> 1:27:39.958
Oh, it's...

1:27:40.708 --> 1:27:42.041
It's purely survival.

1:27:42.125 --> 1:27:43.875
-Purely survival?
-Yeah.

1:28:21.250 --> 1:28:23.083
-[beeps]
-[man] Hello?

1:28:23.958 --> 1:28:24.833
Hello?

1:28:25.666 --> 1:28:27.625
Is anyone there? Hello?

1:28:27.708 --> 1:28:28.833
[static]

1:28:29.750 --> 1:28:30.875
Testing. Testing.

1:28:30.958 --> 1:28:33.916
If there is anyone there, please respond.

1:28:34.000 --> 1:28:35.625
-Hello?
-[Tom] Hello.

1:28:35.708 --> 1:28:37.125
Who is this?

1:28:37.208 --> 1:28:39.041
My name is Rick.

1:28:39.708 --> 1:28:40.625
Who is this?

1:28:43.166 --> 1:28:44.375
Rick, this is Tom.

1:28:44.458 --> 1:28:45.791
We have a place.

1:28:45.875 --> 1:28:48.416
A compound with enough supplies--

1:28:48.500 --> 1:28:49.833
[static]

1:28:49.916 --> 1:28:50.916
We have a community.

1:28:52.041 --> 1:28:53.625
It's safe here.

1:28:54.416 --> 1:28:56.666
We're down by the river's end.

1:28:56.750 --> 1:28:59.041
-Where are you?
-[whispers] Don't answer that.

1:29:00.125 --> 1:29:01.541
Near Pike's Quarry.

1:29:02.125 --> 1:29:05.666
Jesus. You're a ways away.
How many of you are there?

1:29:06.583 --> 1:29:08.333
-Four of us.
-Hmm-mm.

1:29:08.416 --> 1:29:09.958
Are any of them children?

1:29:10.041 --> 1:29:12.583
-Don't, do not say anything.
-It's okay. It's okay.

1:29:13.750 --> 1:29:16.125
No. Why?

1:29:17.000 --> 1:29:19.625
Because the fastest way
to get here is by the river,

1:29:19.708 --> 1:29:22.416
and I don't think
you could make it with kids.

1:29:23.125 --> 1:29:24.708
[Tom] Wait, the river?

1:29:25.291 --> 1:29:27.041
Float downstream as far as you can.

1:29:27.125 --> 1:29:29.291
Stay on the water
until you hit the rapids.

1:29:30.208 --> 1:29:32.583
The water is fast there. It's dangerous.

1:29:33.125 --> 1:29:34.416
We've lost some people.

1:29:35.291 --> 1:29:37.375
You need to see clearly.

1:29:37.458 --> 1:29:40.083
-What does that mean?
-What do you mean, see clearly?

1:29:41.250 --> 1:29:43.291
You will have to look.

1:29:44.583 --> 1:29:46.833
-I'm telling you.
-Rick, we'll have blindfolds on.

1:29:46.916 --> 1:29:48.083
We can't look.

1:29:48.166 --> 1:29:50.041
I'm glad you said that.

1:29:50.125 --> 1:29:51.833
Someone will have to take a--

1:29:51.916 --> 1:29:53.333
[static]

1:29:53.416 --> 1:29:57.500
Prepare for two days' journey
at the pace of the river's current.

1:29:57.583 --> 1:29:59.166
Bring supplies for longer.

1:29:59.750 --> 1:30:01.875
How do I find you after the rapids, Rick?

1:30:01.958 --> 1:30:03.208
You'll hear the birds.

1:30:03.875 --> 1:30:07.041
We've got a lot of them.
Just follow the sound to us.

1:30:07.125 --> 1:30:10.500
Down a small embankment,
you'll find a wall with a gate.

1:30:10.583 --> 1:30:11.458
That's our--

1:30:11.541 --> 1:30:12.416
[static]

1:30:13.875 --> 1:30:15.333
-That's their what?
-That's our what?

1:30:16.291 --> 1:30:17.166
Rick?

1:30:18.500 --> 1:30:19.458
[Tom] Rick?

1:30:30.791 --> 1:30:31.750
[Tom] It could be real.

1:30:31.833 --> 1:30:32.833
-No.
-Could be the truth.

1:30:32.916 --> 1:30:35.125
-Could be is not good enough.
-What if Rick could help us?

1:30:35.208 --> 1:30:36.833
And what if Rick is one of them?

1:30:37.416 --> 1:30:38.625
Huh?

1:30:38.708 --> 1:30:40.291
Wait, he knew about the birds.

1:30:40.958 --> 1:30:43.708
Oh, my God. Gary knew about the birds
and he put them in the freezer.

1:30:43.791 --> 1:30:46.000
I cannot believe
you're actually thinking about this.

1:30:46.083 --> 1:30:47.958
Every house has run out of food.
We have to move.

1:30:48.041 --> 1:30:51.208
You really don't think I know that?
You don't think I know that?

1:30:56.750 --> 1:30:59.125
When I was little,
we had a boat just like this.

1:30:59.708 --> 1:31:01.958
And every single summer,
we would take it to the lake.

1:31:02.041 --> 1:31:03.000
Every summer.

1:31:03.583 --> 1:31:07.000
You guys would have loved it up there.
They had trees. They had flowers.

1:31:07.583 --> 1:31:10.458
The water was warm,
the clouds were in the sky.

1:31:11.291 --> 1:31:14.125
We'd all play in the water.
All the kids, all the children.

1:31:14.208 --> 1:31:16.208
We would all just run
up and down the shore.

1:31:16.291 --> 1:31:18.250
There were other children in the world?

1:31:19.000 --> 1:31:21.500
Yeah, just like you. Just like you.

1:31:21.583 --> 1:31:23.000
-[giggles]
-Like you.

1:31:23.833 --> 1:31:26.916
[Tom] One day, we saw
this really, really big oak tree.

1:31:27.000 --> 1:31:28.541
It was bigger than this house.

1:31:28.625 --> 1:31:31.083
It was so big and old,
I couldn't see the top of it.

1:31:31.166 --> 1:31:32.583
-Guess what we did?
-Climbed it.

1:31:32.666 --> 1:31:34.291
We climbed it. Yes, we climbed it.

1:31:34.375 --> 1:31:36.750
We climbed it and climbed it
until we got to the top.

1:31:37.708 --> 1:31:39.291
Guess what we saw when we got to the top?

1:31:39.375 --> 1:31:40.875
Boy! Girl! Time for bed.

1:31:40.958 --> 1:31:42.500
But Tom's telling a story.

1:31:42.583 --> 1:31:45.958
-Mal, let me just-- We're almost done.
-I'm not gonna say it again. Come on.

1:31:48.583 --> 1:31:49.541
Girl, come on.

1:31:50.958 --> 1:31:52.083
Right now.

1:31:52.166 --> 1:31:53.125
Come on.

1:31:53.958 --> 1:31:55.416
Right now.

1:31:56.375 --> 1:31:57.250
Bed!

1:31:59.791 --> 1:32:00.750
[door slams]

1:32:00.833 --> 1:32:02.791
-[Malorie] What are you doing?
-What are you doing?

1:32:02.875 --> 1:32:05.958
Now they think they're gonna go outside
and climb trees with all these new kids

1:32:06.041 --> 1:32:08.041
-and see butterflies and flowers!
-It's a story.

1:32:08.125 --> 1:32:10.083
It's not a story. It's a lie.

1:32:10.166 --> 1:32:13.000
Because they'll never climb trees,
they are never gonna make new friends.

1:32:13.083 --> 1:32:15.791
-Why make them believe that?
-They have to believe in something.

1:32:15.875 --> 1:32:18.166
What is this for
if they don't have anything to believe in?

1:32:18.250 --> 1:32:20.416
-So that they survive!
-Surviving is not living.

1:32:20.500 --> 1:32:22.916
They're gonna die if they listen to you!

1:32:25.166 --> 1:32:28.416
Life is more than just what is. It's
what could be. What you could make it.

1:32:28.500 --> 1:32:31.375
You need to promise them dreams
that may never come true.

1:32:31.458 --> 1:32:34.791
You need to love them knowing
that you may lose them at any second.

1:32:34.875 --> 1:32:38.375
They deserve dreams. They deserve love.
They deserve hope. They deserve a mother.

1:32:39.500 --> 1:32:41.375
They deserve a mother.

1:32:41.875 --> 1:32:44.875
You haven't given them names, Mal.
Their names are Boy and Girl!

1:32:44.958 --> 1:32:45.791
Think about that.

1:32:45.875 --> 1:32:48.375
Every single decision I have made
has been for them.

1:32:48.458 --> 1:32:50.625
Every single one.

1:32:53.833 --> 1:32:54.875
[door closes]

1:33:10.625 --> 1:33:12.000
You know what I saw?

1:33:14.291 --> 1:33:15.916
At the top of the tree?

1:33:17.500 --> 1:33:19.041
I saw a nest.

1:33:21.625 --> 1:33:22.958
With five birds.

1:33:23.958 --> 1:33:26.000
Sitting on the top branch.

1:33:30.833 --> 1:33:32.375
And then they just flew away.

1:33:58.125 --> 1:34:00.333
[whispers] Got it. Got it. Sit. Sit!

1:34:29.791 --> 1:34:31.166
[Tom] It's safe. Come in.

1:35:05.041 --> 1:35:06.000
Wow.

1:35:06.083 --> 1:35:07.583
No, you did not.

1:35:08.750 --> 1:35:11.375
-They're probably stale.
-Yeah.

1:35:12.333 --> 1:35:13.416
Come here.

1:35:14.666 --> 1:35:15.916
Just how I like 'em.

1:35:17.083 --> 1:35:18.083
I'm sorry.

1:35:20.416 --> 1:35:22.250
-Sorry.
-Me too.

1:35:25.041 --> 1:35:25.958
Come here.

1:35:42.375 --> 1:35:43.583
[Tom] Kids.

1:35:47.750 --> 1:35:49.500
[Malorie] This is strawberry.

1:35:49.583 --> 1:35:51.625
This is what strawberry tastes like.

1:35:55.708 --> 1:35:57.083
[laughs]

1:36:05.583 --> 1:36:07.500
[tires squeal]

1:36:07.583 --> 1:36:09.333
-What's that?
-Quiet.

1:36:09.416 --> 1:36:11.458
[vehicle approaching]

1:36:14.666 --> 1:36:15.708
Shh.

1:36:17.666 --> 1:36:18.708
[man] Anybody home?

1:36:20.000 --> 1:36:21.083
[gunshot]

1:36:21.166 --> 1:36:23.500
[Tom] Take the kids out the back.
I'll distract them.

1:36:23.583 --> 1:36:26.458
If I'm not home in 15 minutes,
you take the kids to the boat and you go.

1:36:26.541 --> 1:36:28.125
-I'm not leaving you!
-Mal.

1:36:28.208 --> 1:36:30.375
-No, I'm not leaving you.
-Listen to me.

1:36:31.333 --> 1:36:32.833
I love you so much.

1:36:34.625 --> 1:36:36.291
I love you. Go.

1:36:36.375 --> 1:36:38.250
-No!
-Go. Please go.

1:36:38.958 --> 1:36:40.083
Be good. Go.

1:36:40.625 --> 1:36:41.458
Go!

1:36:41.541 --> 1:36:42.708
[Tom] I'm coming out!

1:36:44.791 --> 1:36:47.458
-[man] Hey there, friend.
-Can I help you?

1:36:49.458 --> 1:36:50.708
I don't think so, friend.

1:36:50.791 --> 1:36:52.125
We can help you though.

1:36:52.208 --> 1:36:53.666
[Tom] No. Go!

1:36:54.291 --> 1:36:56.416
-Take off your blindfold.
-Stand back.

1:36:56.500 --> 1:36:58.458
-Stand back!
-She's not moving.

1:37:03.708 --> 1:37:05.541
Hey. Got a woman and two kids over here.

1:37:19.708 --> 1:37:20.916
They're coming.

1:37:22.000 --> 1:37:23.250
They won't hurt you.

1:37:23.333 --> 1:37:25.041
Fuck it. Fuck it.

1:37:26.208 --> 1:37:27.416
On the contrary...

1:37:29.041 --> 1:37:31.041
it's a beautiful thing, friend.

1:37:53.750 --> 1:37:55.375
[wind whistles]

1:37:56.791 --> 1:37:58.125
[distorted whispers]

1:38:01.291 --> 1:38:03.291
[rumbling]

1:38:15.291 --> 1:38:17.250
[panting]

1:38:23.166 --> 1:38:24.166
[gunshot]

1:39:13.208 --> 1:39:14.708
[weeping]

1:39:22.000 --> 1:39:24.000
[breathing heavily]

1:39:42.041 --> 1:39:43.250
[sniffles]

1:39:53.416 --> 1:39:56.833
[Malorie] Listen to me.
I'm only gonna say this once.

1:39:56.916 --> 1:39:59.708
We are going on the trip now.
It's going to be rough.

1:39:59.791 --> 1:40:04.458
You have to do every single thing I say
or we will not make it.

1:40:04.541 --> 1:40:05.708
Understand?

1:40:06.916 --> 1:40:08.083
[Girl] Where's Tom?

1:40:09.166 --> 1:40:10.291
He's not coming.

1:40:28.083 --> 1:40:30.750
It's time. It's time. It's time.

1:40:44.458 --> 1:40:45.625
You remember the rapids?

1:40:46.708 --> 1:40:48.708
Remember I told you about the rapids?

1:40:50.250 --> 1:40:51.208
Well, they're close.

1:40:51.291 --> 1:40:56.541
It is very dangerous and there's only
one way for me to navigate through them.

1:40:57.541 --> 1:40:58.625
Somebody has to look.

1:40:59.208 --> 1:41:01.583
-I'll look.
-No. I will decide! Okay? I will decide.

1:41:01.666 --> 1:41:03.541
Just give me-- Just give me a second.

1:41:11.375 --> 1:41:12.250
I'll do it.

1:41:41.916 --> 1:41:43.500
I love you so much.

1:41:51.500 --> 1:41:52.583
[grunts]

1:41:53.500 --> 1:41:54.625
Nobody's looking.

1:41:56.000 --> 1:41:57.041
Okay, nobody's looking.

1:41:58.250 --> 1:41:59.250
Okay?

1:42:09.791 --> 1:42:11.333
Do your eyes. Let's do eyes.

1:42:17.791 --> 1:42:20.916
[Malorie] Come on. Get on your knees.
Stay down low. Hold on tight.

1:42:21.000 --> 1:42:22.666
Don't move. Hold tight.

1:42:38.541 --> 1:42:41.416
[Malorie] Hold tight. Don't let go.
We're gonna be okay.

